1
00:00:32,748 --> 00:00:36,248
(After reading the script in the 4th lesson,)

2
00:00:37,618 --> 00:00:40,557
(the final roles have been decided after much deliberation.)

3
00:00:40,558 --> 00:00:42,827
- The Scarecrow.
- Hyo Min.

4
00:00:42,828 --> 00:00:44,728
(Hyo Min, who didn't get the role he wanted,)

5
00:00:46,358 --> 00:00:49,798
(shed tears of disappointment.)

6
00:00:50,998 --> 00:00:53,298
(I was heartbroken.)

7
00:00:53,808 --> 00:00:55,468
(And...)

8
00:00:56,008 --> 00:00:58,138
(at a dumbfounding timing,)

9
00:00:58,808 --> 00:01:01,148
(Kangnam came from the North Pole.)

10
00:01:01,848 --> 00:01:04,918
(The 5th lesson is with North Pole Teacher.)

11
00:01:06,618 --> 00:01:10,388
(What will happen today?)

12
00:01:12,658 --> 00:01:16,558
(Going back in time...)

13
00:01:17,658 --> 00:01:21,598
(to the morning before the roles were decided)

14
00:01:22,268 --> 00:01:23,498
I'm screwed, Hyo Min.

15
00:01:23,568 --> 00:01:24,937
- Why?
- I couldn't...

16
00:01:24,938 --> 00:01:26,298
record myself practicing.

17
00:01:27,968 --> 00:01:29,138
Do you know what I did?

18
00:01:29,168 --> 00:01:32,477
I went home, ate, took a shower,

19
00:01:32,478 --> 00:01:33,808
- I took one.
- and slept.

20
00:01:34,208 --> 00:01:36,278
- I should've helped you.
- I took it alone.

21
00:01:36,348 --> 00:01:37,548
I should've helped you.

22
00:01:37,918 --> 00:01:38,978
When did you take it?

23
00:01:40,218 --> 00:01:41,647
"It's dazzling."

24
00:01:41,648 --> 00:01:43,047
(Hyo Min's practice video)

25
00:01:43,048 --> 00:01:44,188
"The scent of flowers."

26
00:01:45,218 --> 00:01:47,427
"I'll help you get down!"

27
00:01:47,428 --> 00:01:49,728
(He diligently practiced Toto.)

28
00:01:50,898 --> 00:01:53,127
What role did you get, Hyo Min?

29
00:01:53,128 --> 00:01:54,498
The Scarecrow.

30
00:01:55,728 --> 00:01:58,798
I wanted to be Toto, but I was assigned the role...

31
00:01:59,038 --> 00:02:00,098
of the Scarecrow.

32
00:02:00,968 --> 00:02:02,467
How did you feel?

33
00:02:02,468 --> 00:02:04,138
I felt a little lost.

34
00:02:04,378 --> 00:02:05,538
Did you feel lost?

35
00:02:06,238 --> 00:02:08,677
Because I was suddenly told to play the Scarecrow...

36
00:02:08,678 --> 00:02:10,618
when I had worked hard on being Toto.

37
00:02:11,648 --> 00:02:13,218
Were you not sad or anything?

38
00:02:13,578 --> 00:02:15,348
I'm over...

39
00:02:15,648 --> 00:02:16,688
being sad now.

40
00:02:16,918 --> 00:02:18,188
How come?

41
00:02:18,988 --> 00:02:21,988
I've already recovered from it.

42
00:02:23,958 --> 00:02:26,057
Do you like the Scarecrow now?

43
00:02:26,058 --> 00:02:29,598
(Do you like the Scarecrow now?)

44
00:02:31,668 --> 00:02:36,008
(Will Hyo Min open his heart to the Scarecrow?)

45
00:02:37,338 --> 00:02:39,878
Today is the fifth class.

46
00:02:41,678 --> 00:02:43,147
(The students are hanging out before the acting class.)

47
00:02:43,148 --> 00:02:44,578
Do you want me to throw it hard or gently?

48
00:02:44,778 --> 00:02:46,448
- Over here.
- Don't throw it too hard.

49
00:02:47,388 --> 00:02:49,788
- It's Potato Teacher.
- Potato Teacher.

50
00:02:50,218 --> 00:02:51,917
- Hello!
- Potato Teacher!

51
00:02:51,918 --> 00:02:53,558
Potato Teacher, I have something for you.

52
00:02:54,628 --> 00:02:55,628
What is it?

53
00:02:55,629 --> 00:02:56,757
You're wearing...

54
00:02:56,758 --> 00:02:58,058
- a granny's outfit today.
- Right?

55
00:02:58,628 --> 00:03:00,098
- Here, Mr. Choi.
- What is it?

56
00:03:00,198 --> 00:03:01,597
- It's for you.
- Madeleine.

57
00:03:01,598 --> 00:03:02,628
- Madeleine.
- Is it for me?

58
00:03:02,898 --> 00:03:04,968
Thank you so much. You guys are the best.

59
00:03:05,598 --> 00:03:06,968
Where are we going?

60
00:03:07,368 --> 00:03:09,168
Turn left.

61
00:03:09,308 --> 00:03:10,578
Left.

62
00:03:10,738 --> 00:03:12,337
- What's this?
- Are we going on a picnic?

63
00:03:12,338 --> 00:03:13,537
- It's delicious.
- Good, right?

64
00:03:13,538 --> 00:03:17,248
We made the batter and baked it ourselves.

65
00:03:17,318 --> 00:03:19,447
He's right. It's fueled with our love.

66
00:03:19,448 --> 00:03:20,587
- Really?
- Pay us five dollars.

67
00:03:20,588 --> 00:03:22,918
It should be "filled," not "fueled."

68
00:03:23,688 --> 00:03:24,957
Where's Ms. Kim?

69
00:03:24,958 --> 00:03:26,057
Are we taking the car?

70
00:03:26,058 --> 00:03:27,058
No.

71
00:03:27,758 --> 00:03:30,258
Our class is outdoors today.

72
00:03:31,598 --> 00:03:34,428
The teachers will be living here for two weeks.

73
00:03:34,668 --> 00:03:36,027
- Here?
- Yes.

74
00:03:36,028 --> 00:03:37,197
I'm opening the door with one hand.

75
00:03:37,198 --> 00:03:38,997
- In 1, 2, 3.
- Knock, knock.

76
00:03:38,998 --> 00:03:40,407
- Knock, knock.
- Knock, knock.

77
00:03:40,408 --> 00:03:42,307
- Knock, knock.
- Excuse me.

78
00:03:42,308 --> 00:03:43,667
- Ms. Kim.
- Excuse me.

79
00:03:43,668 --> 00:03:45,477
- Hi.
- Hi.

80
00:03:45,478 --> 00:03:47,107
- Excuse me.
- Ms. Kim.

81
00:03:47,108 --> 00:03:50,007
- Welcome.
- Come in.

82
00:03:50,008 --> 00:03:51,718
- I have something for you.
- Me too.

83
00:03:51,818 --> 00:03:53,377
Welcome.

84
00:03:53,378 --> 00:03:54,487
(North Pole Teacher is hiding to surprise them.)

85
00:03:54,488 --> 00:03:55,717
I have something for you.

86
00:03:55,718 --> 00:03:57,417
Really? It's a bear!

87
00:03:57,418 --> 00:03:59,088
- Thanks.
- Ms. Kim.

88
00:03:59,888 --> 00:04:01,288
Why is it so cozy here?

89
00:04:01,458 --> 00:04:02,488
Thanks.

90
00:04:03,288 --> 00:04:04,398
I like it here.

91
00:04:05,458 --> 00:04:07,967
Shall we start by chanting first?

92
00:04:07,968 --> 00:04:08,968
Okay.

93
00:04:09,228 --> 00:04:12,068
From today, we are one. We can do it. Let's go.

94
00:04:12,168 --> 00:04:13,638
What should we say after that?

95
00:04:14,208 --> 00:04:15,507
- Go!
- "Go?"

96
00:04:15,508 --> 00:04:17,407
- Yes.
- Let's end it with "go" today,

97
00:04:17,408 --> 00:04:18,478
- Go!
- okay?

98
00:04:19,538 --> 00:04:22,678
From today, we are...

99
00:04:23,078 --> 00:04:24,718
one!

100
00:04:25,218 --> 00:04:27,687
- We can do it!
- We can do it!

101
00:04:27,688 --> 00:04:30,318
- Let's go. Go!
- Let's go. Go!

102
00:04:31,258 --> 00:04:32,988
(Nervous)

103
00:04:33,788 --> 00:04:35,458
The students are enthusiastic.

104
00:04:36,828 --> 00:04:38,398
Today's warm-up will be...

105
00:04:38,698 --> 00:04:40,868
Remember the roles you were given yesterday?

106
00:04:41,568 --> 00:04:42,767
What were you again, Do Hyun?

107
00:04:42,768 --> 00:04:44,038
The Tin Man.

108
00:04:44,098 --> 00:04:45,598
- Kyung Mo?
- Toto.

109
00:04:45,698 --> 00:04:46,738
- Toto.
- Ha Yun?

110
00:04:46,998 --> 00:04:50,238
- I'm the Wizard and the Gatekeeper.
- The Wizard and the Gatekeeper.

111
00:04:50,878 --> 00:04:52,208
- Hyo Min?
- The Scarecrow.

112
00:04:52,308 --> 00:04:53,878
- The Scarecrow?
- The Scarecrow.

113
00:04:53,948 --> 00:04:55,248
- The Scarecrow.
- Ju Eun?

114
00:04:55,408 --> 00:04:57,148
The Witch, Munchkin, and narrator.

115
00:04:57,278 --> 00:04:58,347
- The Wicked Witch of the West, yes?
- The Witch, Munchkin,

116
00:04:58,348 --> 00:04:59,417
- and narrator.
- Won Jin?

117
00:04:59,418 --> 00:05:00,447
The Lion.

118
00:05:00,448 --> 00:05:01,618
- The Lion.
- Eun Soo?

119
00:05:02,688 --> 00:05:03,688
Dorothy.

120
00:05:03,689 --> 00:05:04,857
- Dorothy.
- Dorothy.

121
00:05:04,858 --> 00:05:07,187
Today, we're going to walk around...

122
00:05:07,188 --> 00:05:09,527
in the role you were given.

123
00:05:09,528 --> 00:05:10,528
(Imagining how each role would walk)

124
00:05:10,529 --> 00:05:14,498
Hyo Min, how would the Scarecrow walk?

125
00:05:19,498 --> 00:05:20,668
The Scarecrow.

126
00:05:21,508 --> 00:05:22,907
How would the Scarecrow walk?

127
00:05:22,908 --> 00:05:24,138
Like this, right?

128
00:05:24,208 --> 00:05:25,708
The Scarecrow on a rod.

129
00:05:26,478 --> 00:05:27,807
What about Dorothy, Eun Soo?

130
00:05:27,808 --> 00:05:29,247
- How about this?
- Yes?

131
00:05:29,248 --> 00:05:32,018
Let's give our students about two minutes to think.

132
00:05:33,048 --> 00:05:35,187
(Thinking)

133
00:05:35,188 --> 00:05:36,788
I'll help.

134
00:05:37,458 --> 00:05:38,688
Hyo Min, come here.

135
00:05:38,818 --> 00:05:41,187
You need to be the Scarecrow for the whole day.

136
00:05:41,188 --> 00:05:43,288
We can't have you all gloomy already.

137
00:05:43,428 --> 00:05:45,628
- Come. I'll help.
- I came prepared.

138
00:05:46,128 --> 00:05:47,827
I'm already prepared.

139
00:05:47,828 --> 00:05:49,297
- You're already prepared?
- Yes.

140
00:05:49,298 --> 00:05:51,937
- How cool. Really?
- Yes.

141
00:05:51,938 --> 00:05:53,597
I'm really curious.

142
00:05:53,598 --> 00:05:54,937
(Praiseworthy)

143
00:05:54,938 --> 00:05:57,338
Even so, here's a small hint.

144
00:05:57,808 --> 00:05:59,607
- It'd be light, right?
- Can it be burned in a fire?

145
00:05:59,608 --> 00:06:02,348
Yes, imagine a reed.

146
00:06:03,278 --> 00:06:04,718
- That's right.
- Isn't it immortal?

147
00:06:04,878 --> 00:06:07,288
Yes, the Scarecrow might be immortal.

148
00:06:07,518 --> 00:06:08,518
Up there...

149
00:06:15,228 --> 00:06:16,228
Look over there.

150
00:06:16,229 --> 00:06:18,098
Someone's riding a bicycle in the back.

151
00:06:18,498 --> 00:06:20,458
Someone's riding a bicycle in the back.

152
00:06:22,198 --> 00:06:25,738
(His bicycle has entered during class.)

153
00:06:27,268 --> 00:06:28,338
Who...

154
00:06:28,738 --> 00:06:31,738
(His guard is up fully.)

155
00:06:32,338 --> 00:06:33,677
The rose of Sharon.

156
00:06:33,678 --> 00:06:35,348
(Studying the faces)

157
00:06:35,848 --> 00:06:37,107
- The name...
- The rose of Sharon

158
00:06:37,108 --> 00:06:39,178
Excuse me, you can't come in here.

159
00:06:40,548 --> 00:06:41,618
Who are you?

160
00:06:43,148 --> 00:06:44,658
(Laughing)

161
00:06:44,958 --> 00:06:46,358
This is a restricted area.

162
00:06:47,558 --> 00:06:48,558
Guys.

163
00:06:48,828 --> 00:06:50,528
What's the opposite of the South Pole?

164
00:06:50,758 --> 00:06:51,827
- The North Pole.
- The North Pole.

165
00:06:51,828 --> 00:06:53,398
- The North Pole.
- North Teacher?

166
00:06:53,998 --> 00:06:55,627
Sir, stop.

167
00:06:55,628 --> 00:06:56,667
(An excellent actor)

168
00:06:56,668 --> 00:06:58,368
Come over here for a minute.

169
00:06:58,968 --> 00:07:01,337
- Who is he?
- He's our new teacher.

170
00:07:01,338 --> 00:07:02,437
You're right.

171
00:07:02,438 --> 00:07:04,538
Who are you to keep wandering around?

172
00:07:04,738 --> 00:07:05,907
- Really?
- I'm sorry.

173
00:07:05,908 --> 00:07:07,007
What are you here for?

174
00:07:07,008 --> 00:07:08,477
- I was just passing by. Sorry.
- Is that so?

175
00:07:08,478 --> 00:07:09,977
- Sorry.
- He's our new teacher.

176
00:07:09,978 --> 00:07:11,748
- Sorry.
- Our new teacher, right?

177
00:07:12,548 --> 00:07:13,677
- Introduce yourself.
- Okay.

178
00:07:13,678 --> 00:07:15,488
Hi, I'm your new teacher.

179
00:07:16,088 --> 00:07:17,317
- Where are you from?
- Seriously?

180
00:07:17,318 --> 00:07:18,687
- I'm from the North Pole.
- What?

181
00:07:18,688 --> 00:07:20,517
- He's from the North Pole.
- That's right.

182
00:07:20,518 --> 00:07:22,227
Hi, I'm your new teacher.

183
00:07:22,228 --> 00:07:23,228
(Laughing)

184
00:07:23,229 --> 00:07:24,498
Seriously?

185
00:07:24,658 --> 00:07:26,798
I actually thought he was trespassing.

186
00:07:27,798 --> 00:07:29,427
I thought he was a trespasser.

187
00:07:29,428 --> 00:07:30,737
(The students fell for it.)

188
00:07:30,738 --> 00:07:32,097
- I'm your new teacher.
- Guys.

189
00:07:32,098 --> 00:07:34,367
His name is North Pole Teacher.

190
00:07:34,368 --> 00:07:36,367
- That's right.
- Call him North Pole Teacher.

191
00:07:36,368 --> 00:07:38,838
I'm North Pole Teacher. Please take good care of me.

192
00:07:39,208 --> 00:07:42,447
(Welcome!)

193
00:07:42,448 --> 00:07:44,918
Here's what we're going to do today.

194
00:07:45,648 --> 00:07:46,678
"Create..."

195
00:07:47,618 --> 00:07:48,618
"a..."

196
00:07:49,288 --> 00:07:52,458
- "scene." - I don't get it.

197
00:07:53,318 --> 00:07:55,087
This will be our stage.

198
00:07:55,088 --> 00:07:57,697
You will actually act it out.

199
00:07:57,698 --> 00:08:01,928
The scene we'll try out is on page 12.

200
00:08:02,428 --> 00:08:04,398
The Witch throws fire at Dorothy's friends,

201
00:08:04,838 --> 00:08:08,368
kidnaps Dorothy from them, and leaves.

202
00:08:08,608 --> 00:08:10,468
- That's the scene, okay?
- It's an important one.

203
00:08:11,078 --> 00:08:12,138
The narrator.

204
00:08:13,278 --> 00:08:15,577
The narrator is in front of the curtain.

205
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:16,647
(Starting with the narration)

206
00:08:16,648 --> 00:08:18,417
She's going to read her lines.

207
00:08:18,418 --> 00:08:19,578
- Go ahead.
- Start.

208
00:08:20,348 --> 00:08:23,348
"However, their peaceful journey didn't last for long."

209
00:08:23,488 --> 00:08:28,128
"What has happened to Dorothy and her friends?"

210
00:08:28,288 --> 00:08:31,128
When the music plays, the Witch...

211
00:08:32,028 --> 00:08:34,497
will wear her hat and cloak.

212
00:08:34,498 --> 00:08:37,127
- After that, the curtain opens.
- I'm opening it.

213
00:08:37,128 --> 00:08:38,497
Once it opens,

214
00:08:38,498 --> 00:08:40,438
who should be on stage?

215
00:08:41,308 --> 00:08:42,337
Toto Kyung Mo.

216
00:08:42,338 --> 00:08:44,238
Toto Kyung Mo and the Scarecrow Hyo Min.

217
00:08:44,438 --> 00:08:46,808
Dorothy. The Tin Man.

218
00:08:47,238 --> 00:08:49,408
- The Lion should also be on stage.
- You know, right, Wizard?

219
00:08:49,608 --> 00:08:50,608
- Yes.
- Wizard.

220
00:08:50,609 --> 00:08:52,247
The cool Wizard appears last.

221
00:08:52,248 --> 00:08:53,248
- You're important.
- Yes.

222
00:08:53,249 --> 00:08:56,147
The Wizard... The main character always appears last.

223
00:08:56,148 --> 00:08:58,788
Let's watch them perform together.

224
00:08:59,018 --> 00:09:00,317
Open to page 12 first.

225
00:09:00,318 --> 00:09:01,588
- Guys.
- Page 12.

226
00:09:02,328 --> 00:09:04,958
You'll know how to act only when you watch them.

227
00:09:05,228 --> 00:09:06,298
- Right?
- Yes.

228
00:09:07,028 --> 00:09:08,668
The curtain opens.

229
00:09:08,998 --> 00:09:10,597
It's a dark forest.

230
00:09:10,598 --> 00:09:14,238
All right, Toto and his friends enter.

231
00:09:15,108 --> 00:09:16,167
(Toto)

232
00:09:16,168 --> 00:09:17,878
"I can smell fire."

233
00:09:18,278 --> 00:09:19,377
"Dorothy,"

234
00:09:19,378 --> 00:09:21,378
- "we finally meet." - Good.

235
00:09:21,708 --> 00:09:25,147
"I knew you'd be on your way to meet the Wizard of Oz."

236
00:09:25,148 --> 00:09:27,417
- She's good.
- Okay, Dorothy.

237
00:09:27,418 --> 00:09:30,318
"Could you be the Wicked Witch of the West?"

238
00:09:30,988 --> 00:09:33,318
"That's right. I'm the Wicked Witch of the West."

239
00:09:33,658 --> 00:09:37,357
"Killing your younger sister..."

240
00:09:37,358 --> 00:09:38,928
"was a coincidence."

241
00:09:39,058 --> 00:09:40,298
"The house fell..."

242
00:09:40,928 --> 00:09:43,298
"on top of her because of the tornado."

243
00:09:44,798 --> 00:09:46,467
"The details don't matter."

244
00:09:46,468 --> 00:09:47,768
"What I want is..."

245
00:09:48,638 --> 00:09:50,068
"your silver shoes."

246
00:09:50,738 --> 00:09:51,738
Toto.

247
00:09:52,678 --> 00:09:54,077
"Don't desire it."

248
00:09:54,078 --> 00:09:55,647
- That's it.
- Great.

249
00:09:55,648 --> 00:09:56,708
- Nice.
- Great.

250
00:09:57,578 --> 00:10:01,888
When the Witch makes a sound effect,

251
00:10:02,118 --> 00:10:06,158
the fire lands between Dorothy and her friends.

252
00:10:06,658 --> 00:10:07,987
(The Witch attacks.)

253
00:10:07,988 --> 00:10:09,128
Here it goes.

254
00:10:10,228 --> 00:10:11,228
Here.

255
00:10:11,229 --> 00:10:12,757
(The Witch's attack succeeds.)

256
00:10:12,758 --> 00:10:14,928
Toto and the Lion are together.

257
00:10:15,128 --> 00:10:16,768
Dorothy is being kidnapped.

258
00:10:16,868 --> 00:10:18,438
Drop down, Scarecrow!

259
00:10:18,868 --> 00:10:20,567
The Scarecrow has been knocked down.

260
00:10:20,568 --> 00:10:21,767
The Tin Man has to shout.

261
00:10:21,768 --> 00:10:22,868
- Shout.
- Go ahead, Tin Man.

262
00:10:23,068 --> 00:10:24,978
Dorothy!

263
00:10:25,138 --> 00:10:27,037
With that, the curtain closes.

264
00:10:27,038 --> 00:10:29,248
- The curtain closes.
- The curtain closes.

265
00:10:29,578 --> 00:10:32,218
That's the end of the scene, guys. How was it?

266
00:10:33,118 --> 00:10:34,288
Can you remember it?

267
00:10:35,418 --> 00:10:36,418
Did you know?

268
00:10:36,419 --> 00:10:37,987
- It's break time now.
- What is it?

269
00:10:37,988 --> 00:10:39,788
- Break time.
- I'm going to drink some water.

270
00:10:40,858 --> 00:10:41,928
Let's play baseball.

271
00:10:42,358 --> 00:10:44,197
Here. Throw it to me.

272
00:10:44,198 --> 00:10:45,297
- Here.
- You don't have a glove?

273
00:10:45,298 --> 00:10:46,658
- No, I don't need one.
- Can I try it?

274
00:10:47,158 --> 00:10:48,228
Throw it hard.

275
00:10:49,428 --> 00:10:50,468
Throw it hard.

276
00:10:51,838 --> 00:10:52,968
- Nice.
- Okay.

277
00:10:53,498 --> 00:10:54,838
Cool.

278
00:10:55,638 --> 00:10:57,208
- That's how you catch it.
- Strike!

279
00:10:57,708 --> 00:10:58,778
No, it's a ball.

280
00:11:01,808 --> 00:11:03,108
How are you so good at catching?

281
00:11:03,908 --> 00:11:04,947
- Me?
- Yes.

282
00:11:04,948 --> 00:11:06,077
This is my glove.

283
00:11:06,078 --> 00:11:07,988
- You have to catch it like this.
- Mr. Choi.

284
00:11:08,648 --> 00:11:09,648
- I want to try it.
- What?

285
00:11:09,649 --> 00:11:11,487
- I want to try riding it.
- Why?

286
00:11:11,488 --> 00:11:13,688
- Try riding what?
- The bicycle.

287
00:11:14,258 --> 00:11:16,388
I want to try riding it.

288
00:11:17,028 --> 00:11:19,728
- Jang Won Jin.
- I'm good at riding a bicycle.

289
00:11:20,198 --> 00:11:22,228
Do you want to ride it together, Won Jin?

290
00:11:22,998 --> 00:11:24,238
There's a seat right here.

291
00:11:26,498 --> 00:11:28,168
- Can you ride a bicycle?
- Help me down.

292
00:11:28,568 --> 00:11:29,667
I can.

293
00:11:29,668 --> 00:11:30,808
- Really?
- Help me down.

294
00:11:31,038 --> 00:11:32,877
- Someone looks happy.
- Help me up.

295
00:11:32,878 --> 00:11:34,607
- Help you up here?
- Yes.

296
00:11:34,608 --> 00:11:35,608
Be careful.

297
00:11:35,609 --> 00:11:38,648
(Let's ride it together, Eun Soo.)

298
00:11:39,878 --> 00:11:41,047
- Is it fun?
- Yes.

299
00:11:41,048 --> 00:11:43,217
(Eun Soo and Won Jin's trip together)

300
00:11:43,218 --> 00:11:44,888
I want to ride it myself.

301
00:11:46,388 --> 00:11:48,187
(Taking care of them closely so that they don't get hurt)

302
00:11:48,188 --> 00:11:49,228
Together.

303
00:11:49,488 --> 00:11:51,928
Don't hold on to the brake.

304
00:11:52,128 --> 00:11:54,367
- Are you two the closest?
- We're a bit close.

305
00:11:54,368 --> 00:11:55,698
A bit close? She said a bit close.

306
00:11:56,798 --> 00:11:59,238
Treat your current friends well. They last forever.

307
00:12:01,138 --> 00:12:02,308
He's not even listening.

308
00:12:04,308 --> 00:12:05,907
Let's get back to class.

309
00:12:05,908 --> 00:12:07,078
The class is starting. Let's go.

310
00:12:07,438 --> 00:12:08,678
Sit on your seats.

311
00:12:09,448 --> 00:12:10,748
Sit.

312
00:12:11,418 --> 00:12:13,178
- Page 13.
- Page 13.

313
00:12:13,378 --> 00:12:15,288
- The big lake.
- Page 13.

314
00:12:15,748 --> 00:12:17,787
This time, the teachers will perform,

315
00:12:17,788 --> 00:12:19,157
not you guys.

316
00:12:19,158 --> 00:12:21,958
Potato Teacher, North Pole Teacher. Please help.

317
00:12:22,288 --> 00:12:23,288
- Okay.
- Okay.

318
00:12:23,289 --> 00:12:27,027
The Witch and Dorothy are fighting over here.

319
00:12:27,028 --> 00:12:29,467
It's to take the silver shoes. "No, give them back!"

320
00:12:29,468 --> 00:12:30,827
- Something like that, okay?
- Yes.

321
00:12:30,828 --> 00:12:33,938
From the other side, Dorothy's friends appear.

322
00:12:35,468 --> 00:12:36,708
How would they walk?

323
00:12:36,908 --> 00:12:39,178
They must've rushed over, right? How about breathing hard?

324
00:12:39,908 --> 00:12:41,178
Okay, they've arrived.

325
00:12:41,348 --> 00:12:45,678
The friends notice the Witch and Dorothy fighting.

326
00:12:45,848 --> 00:12:48,448
The friends discuss.

327
00:12:48,688 --> 00:12:51,718
Discuss how they can rescue Dorothy.

328
00:12:51,918 --> 00:12:53,558
You know the lines, right?

329
00:12:53,958 --> 00:12:55,158
How do they do it?

330
00:12:56,088 --> 00:12:59,798
What did the smart Scarecrow think of?

331
00:13:01,268 --> 00:13:04,638
(Quiet)

332
00:13:05,598 --> 00:13:06,598
(Scarecrow)

333
00:13:06,599 --> 00:13:08,038
"The Wicked Witch of the West..."

334
00:13:08,738 --> 00:13:12,778
"uses fire. So if we use water, she will disappear."

335
00:13:14,948 --> 00:13:16,377
(Looking for the lines in a hurry)

336
00:13:16,378 --> 00:13:17,608
The Tin Man...

337
00:13:19,378 --> 00:13:21,917
(Spaced out)

338
00:13:21,918 --> 00:13:23,187
What did he think of?

339
00:13:23,188 --> 00:13:25,257
(Are you listening, guys?)

340
00:13:25,258 --> 00:13:26,917
"The Wicked Witch of the West uses fire."

341
00:13:26,918 --> 00:13:27,927
"So if we use water,"

342
00:13:27,928 --> 00:13:29,127
- "she will disappear." - Right.

343
00:13:29,128 --> 00:13:30,428
That was his idea.

344
00:13:33,128 --> 00:13:34,968
(Sighing)

345
00:13:35,768 --> 00:13:37,168
Does Ju Eun disappear?

346
00:13:37,498 --> 00:13:38,568
No.

347
00:13:38,668 --> 00:13:41,208
Does that make you a different witch?

348
00:13:41,668 --> 00:13:42,908
(Laughing)

349
00:13:46,808 --> 00:13:47,848
No.

350
00:13:47,978 --> 00:13:49,708
She looks like she's lost some weight.

351
00:13:50,878 --> 00:13:52,677
- What is it?
- She's lost some weight.

352
00:13:52,678 --> 00:13:54,818
(Thin and pale even today)

353
00:13:56,348 --> 00:13:57,348
- You're right.
- Hey.

354
00:13:57,349 --> 00:13:59,618
- Why are you excited?
- Guys.

355
00:13:59,718 --> 00:14:02,157
Teachers can make it fun...

356
00:14:02,158 --> 00:14:04,798
only when you focus.

357
00:14:05,328 --> 00:14:07,768
In short, just listen to us,

358
00:14:08,028 --> 00:14:09,028
okay?

359
00:14:10,098 --> 00:14:11,237
- Got it?
- Yes.

360
00:14:11,238 --> 00:14:12,468
- Okay?
- Yes.

361
00:14:12,898 --> 00:14:13,968
Okay?

362
00:14:16,368 --> 00:14:20,807
(The students aren't energetic today.)

363
00:14:20,808 --> 00:14:24,747
Guys, we tried creating a scene today.

364
00:14:24,748 --> 00:14:26,477
We won't see each other...

365
00:14:26,478 --> 00:14:28,348
from Saturday to Monday, right?

366
00:14:28,748 --> 00:14:29,748
We have three days off.

367
00:14:29,749 --> 00:14:32,357
Our next class is on Tuesday.

368
00:14:32,358 --> 00:14:33,787
In other words,

369
00:14:33,788 --> 00:14:36,988
you have to practice hard during the three days.

370
00:14:37,128 --> 00:14:41,728
First, memorize the lines.

371
00:14:41,928 --> 00:14:43,568
- Understood, guys?
- Yes.

372
00:14:43,668 --> 00:14:45,267
- The scene we did today.
- Right.

373
00:14:45,268 --> 00:14:47,267
The scene of defeating the Witch.

374
00:14:47,268 --> 00:14:48,607
Let's try it without the script.

375
00:14:48,608 --> 00:14:50,868
Let's try the scene we did today, okay?

376
00:14:51,178 --> 00:14:52,278
- Yes.
- Good.

377
00:14:53,208 --> 00:14:54,908
Today,

378
00:14:55,678 --> 00:14:57,748
we're going to end the class here.

379
00:14:59,578 --> 00:15:02,048
I do want to play a game like "Red Light, Green Light."

380
00:15:02,988 --> 00:15:03,988
Everyone seems happy.

381
00:15:03,989 --> 00:15:07,218
Guys, this is how we'll play the game.

382
00:15:07,418 --> 00:15:08,557
You will...

383
00:15:08,558 --> 00:15:09,857
(North Pole Teacher will soon become a girl's daddy.)

384
00:15:09,858 --> 00:15:12,657
The game will be played...

385
00:15:12,658 --> 00:15:15,227
by getting into the role.

386
00:15:15,228 --> 00:15:16,268
Okay.

387
00:15:16,728 --> 00:15:18,798
Come on, kids. Let's all do it here.

388
00:15:19,998 --> 00:15:20,998
I want to use this.

389
00:15:20,999 --> 00:15:22,238
- I'll run there.
- Are you keeping the hat?

390
00:15:22,608 --> 00:15:24,168
- That looks difficult.
- Where should we put the line?

391
00:15:24,878 --> 00:15:26,407
It's here.

392
00:15:26,408 --> 00:15:27,638
This is the line, okay?

393
00:15:27,848 --> 00:15:31,078
Instead of saying, "The rose of Sharon has bloomed,"

394
00:15:31,478 --> 00:15:34,248
we're going to say, "The something flower has bloomed."

395
00:15:35,148 --> 00:15:38,887
For instance, when I say, "the tree flower has bloomed,"

396
00:15:38,888 --> 00:15:41,087
how should you stand there?

397
00:15:41,088 --> 00:15:43,258
- Like a tree.
- Like a tree.

398
00:15:43,358 --> 00:15:45,327
That's a tree.

399
00:15:45,328 --> 00:15:47,057
- Isn't this also a tree?
- It sure is.

400
00:15:47,058 --> 00:15:50,598
All right, then. The cat flower has bloomed!

401
00:15:56,238 --> 00:15:57,638
The puppy flower has bloomed!

402
00:15:59,478 --> 00:16:00,838
The puppy flower has bloomed!

403
00:16:00,938 --> 00:16:02,908
(Roaring)

404
00:16:03,678 --> 00:16:05,177
That's one scary puppy.

405
00:16:05,178 --> 00:16:06,318
(Shy)

406
00:16:06,848 --> 00:16:11,287
The lion flower has bloomed!

407
00:16:11,288 --> 00:16:12,288
(Roaring)

408
00:16:14,788 --> 00:16:16,557
The puppies have gotten even scarier.

409
00:16:16,558 --> 00:16:19,298
He moved!

410
00:16:19,628 --> 00:16:21,497
- Who moved?
- Do Hyun!

411
00:16:21,498 --> 00:16:23,627
- Do Hyun, come here.
- Bummer.

412
00:16:23,628 --> 00:16:25,267
- I was moving in secret.
- He also moved.

413
00:16:25,268 --> 00:16:27,968
All right. The witch flower has bloomed!

414
00:16:28,068 --> 00:16:29,537
My hand!

415
00:16:29,538 --> 00:16:31,308
The witch flower has bloomed!

416
00:16:31,608 --> 00:16:35,077
(Cackling)

417
00:16:35,078 --> 00:16:36,307
Cut me off from her!

418
00:16:36,308 --> 00:16:37,507
(A silent scene-stealer)

419
00:16:37,508 --> 00:16:40,278
The Tin Man flower has bloomed!

420
00:16:40,478 --> 00:16:41,887
Cut that quickly.

421
00:16:41,888 --> 00:16:43,748
Look at all these Tin Men.

422
00:16:44,388 --> 00:16:45,518
Next.

423
00:16:46,058 --> 00:16:47,288
- Thank you.
- The Dorothy...

424
00:16:47,818 --> 00:16:49,558
- Hey!
- Let's go!

425
00:16:49,658 --> 00:16:50,658
Catch me if you can.

426
00:16:50,888 --> 00:16:51,928
- Let's go.
- Yes!

427
00:16:53,528 --> 00:16:54,528
I almost got caught.

428
00:16:54,529 --> 00:16:55,997
(Cackling)

429
00:16:55,998 --> 00:16:57,527
Kids, sadly,

430
00:16:57,528 --> 00:16:59,337
- it's time to go home.
- Let's play Freeze Tag.

431
00:16:59,338 --> 00:17:00,338
- Okay.
- Let's play Freeze Tag.

432
00:17:00,339 --> 00:17:01,407
We'll play that next time.

433
00:17:01,408 --> 00:17:03,107
- Thank you.
- Let's go, everyone.

434
00:17:03,108 --> 00:17:04,368
Thank you.

435
00:17:04,468 --> 00:17:06,237
Time to go home!

436
00:17:06,238 --> 00:17:08,008
(A pleasant walk home)

437
00:17:08,478 --> 00:17:11,948
We're going to create a group chatroom...

438
00:17:12,048 --> 00:17:13,378
for practice.

439
00:17:14,648 --> 00:17:16,748
We should call it Acting Class.

440
00:17:16,848 --> 00:17:18,217
Yes, Acting Class.

441
00:17:18,218 --> 00:17:19,518
Get home safely!

442
00:17:19,858 --> 00:17:20,987
Who has KakaoTalk?

443
00:17:20,988 --> 00:17:22,787
- KakaoTalk? Why?
- We all do.

444
00:17:22,788 --> 00:17:24,127
Can I make a group chat?

445
00:17:24,128 --> 00:17:25,697
- Sure.
- Are you for or against it?

446
00:17:25,698 --> 00:17:26,698
- I'm for it.
- I like it.

447
00:17:27,798 --> 00:17:29,168
Hyo Min, are you for it?

448
00:17:29,268 --> 00:17:30,727
- I don't know.
- Is this okay?

449
00:17:30,728 --> 00:17:32,697
So, you're against it.

450
00:17:32,698 --> 00:17:34,668
Do whatever. I'm fine with it.

451
00:17:36,108 --> 00:17:37,338
Was that okay?

452
00:17:38,578 --> 00:17:40,107
- Do you want one?
- You need food.

453
00:17:40,108 --> 00:17:42,407
You lost some weight compared to how you were...

454
00:17:42,408 --> 00:17:43,477
before the class.

455
00:17:43,478 --> 00:17:44,647
(Ms. Kim needs sugar.)

456
00:17:44,648 --> 00:17:47,178
Great work today.

457
00:17:48,418 --> 00:17:49,488
What do we do?

458
00:17:50,388 --> 00:17:52,187
Do you think the kids can memorize the lines?

459
00:17:52,188 --> 00:17:54,827
Today is crucial. They have to memorize a lot.

460
00:17:54,828 --> 00:17:57,088
Or should we change the entire script?

461
00:17:57,188 --> 00:17:58,198
What?

462
00:18:00,228 --> 00:18:01,698
- Now? How?
- The script.

463
00:18:02,128 --> 00:18:03,798
Make it way easier.

464
00:18:03,998 --> 00:18:05,368
Is it too difficult for them?

465
00:18:06,198 --> 00:18:08,007
Yes, let's get some rest first.

466
00:18:08,008 --> 00:18:10,008
- Sure.
- We need a break.

467
00:18:12,608 --> 00:18:15,478
I wrote your name on the notebook, North Pole Teacher.

468
00:18:15,748 --> 00:18:17,908
I was wondering where my notebook was.

469
00:18:18,478 --> 00:18:19,818
Jeez.

470
00:18:20,778 --> 00:18:22,588
Oh, man. I'm starving.

471
00:18:23,318 --> 00:18:24,447
Are we eating dinner right away?

472
00:18:24,448 --> 00:18:25,518
Yes, we have to cook.

473
00:18:26,158 --> 00:18:27,158
It's a party tonight.

474
00:18:27,159 --> 00:18:28,387
(It's a pork belly party tonight.)

475
00:18:28,388 --> 00:18:29,428
This is great.

476
00:18:30,428 --> 00:18:33,258
(Something that goes perfect with pork belly)

477
00:18:33,898 --> 00:18:36,128
(Making scallion salad)

478
00:18:37,568 --> 00:18:40,038
(He chops them like a master.)

479
00:18:41,408 --> 00:18:43,407
(Mix it with Kangnam's special sauce,)

480
00:18:43,408 --> 00:18:45,538
(and the scallion salad is done.)

481
00:18:46,708 --> 00:18:49,508
(Tae Ri will wash the lettuce wraps.)

482
00:18:50,078 --> 00:18:52,177
I'm so happy we don't have a class tomorrow.

483
00:18:52,178 --> 00:18:53,518
(It's a happy weekend tomorrow.)

484
00:18:54,718 --> 00:18:58,418
(The pavilion is open for this Friday night.)

485
00:18:59,418 --> 00:19:02,358
(Hyun Wook will set up the table in the pavilion.)

486
00:19:09,898 --> 00:19:12,398
(He lies down after setting it up.)

487
00:19:14,938 --> 00:19:15,938
(Snoring)

488
00:19:17,838 --> 00:19:18,838
(Snoring)

489
00:19:21,948 --> 00:19:25,148
(Potato Teacher is tired.)

490
00:19:34,358 --> 00:19:37,028
- Is he washing up?
- That's probably it.

491
00:19:38,298 --> 00:19:39,427
That might be it.

492
00:19:39,428 --> 00:19:42,268
(The youngest is sleeping right before her eyes.)

493
00:19:43,498 --> 00:19:44,568
Oh, he's here!

494
00:19:45,568 --> 00:19:46,698
Where? Here?

495
00:19:47,398 --> 00:19:48,708
Oh, he's here?

496
00:19:49,008 --> 00:19:51,008
I thought that was a plastic bag.

497
00:19:52,038 --> 00:19:54,378
(Stealth mode)

498
00:19:55,008 --> 00:19:56,047
Hyun Wook.

499
00:19:56,048 --> 00:19:57,777
(They try to wake him up.)

500
00:19:57,778 --> 00:19:59,248
(Slowly waking up)

501
00:19:59,878 --> 00:20:01,748
- Man.
- He was actually asleep.

502
00:20:04,618 --> 00:20:06,187
- The floor is warm, right?
- Yes.

503
00:20:06,188 --> 00:20:07,318
(Drowsy)

504
00:20:07,918 --> 00:20:09,228
That's so warm.

505
00:20:09,328 --> 00:20:10,388
- Right?
- Yes.

506
00:20:11,088 --> 00:20:13,058
- Should I make the fire?
- Sure.

507
00:20:14,128 --> 00:20:15,828
It burns more easily with pine cones.

508
00:20:16,868 --> 00:20:19,068
(The wood fire is made in seconds.)

509
00:20:20,798 --> 00:20:25,038
(Pork belly cooks nicely on top of it.)

510
00:20:26,338 --> 00:20:28,808
(Everyone is focused on cooking.)

511
00:20:29,608 --> 00:20:32,517
- We're all cooking pork belly.
- I mean,

512
00:20:32,518 --> 00:20:33,917
why are we...

513
00:20:33,918 --> 00:20:35,917
- We're all...
- all cooking separately?

514
00:20:35,918 --> 00:20:37,248
- cooking separately.
- We're supposed to...

515
00:20:39,318 --> 00:20:42,527
As you can tell, I'm not so good at cooking meat.

516
00:20:42,528 --> 00:20:43,627
(Kangnam's barbecue pork belly, Tae Ri's grilled pork belly)

517
00:20:43,628 --> 00:20:47,558
This is a huge responsibility.

518
00:20:48,268 --> 00:20:50,468
(Concentrated)

519
00:20:52,268 --> 00:20:53,637
- That looks good.
- Right?

520
00:20:53,638 --> 00:20:55,208
(Hyun Wook's gochujang pork belly)

521
00:20:55,308 --> 00:20:57,038
Are you finally making gochujang pork belly?

522
00:20:59,038 --> 00:21:02,748
(Cooking Master Potato presents...)

523
00:21:04,708 --> 00:21:06,017
- That's beautiful.
- Awesome, right?

524
00:21:06,018 --> 00:21:07,178
This is insane.

525
00:21:09,088 --> 00:21:11,388
(And Kangnam's secret dish)

526
00:21:11,918 --> 00:21:13,017
It's so...

527
00:21:13,018 --> 00:21:15,328
(Spicy ramyeon)

528
00:21:15,588 --> 00:21:16,787
This is wild.

529
00:21:16,788 --> 00:21:18,728
(Wild)

530
00:21:19,558 --> 00:21:20,628
Smell it.

531
00:21:20,728 --> 00:21:22,028
(Sniffing)

532
00:21:22,128 --> 00:21:24,028
What the heck? Is this from a restaurant?

533
00:21:25,838 --> 00:21:26,838
It smells so good.

534
00:21:28,608 --> 00:21:29,737
That looks scrumptious.

535
00:21:29,738 --> 00:21:30,908
(Perfectly smoky)

536
00:21:31,108 --> 00:21:33,577
- All right.
- Should we eat first?

537
00:21:33,578 --> 00:21:35,448
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you for the food.

538
00:21:35,548 --> 00:21:36,908
This is a good meal.

539
00:21:39,048 --> 00:21:40,148
It's good.

540
00:21:42,418 --> 00:21:45,058
In 1, 2, 3.

541
00:21:46,118 --> 00:21:48,657
(The joy of a Friday night)

542
00:21:48,658 --> 00:21:49,728
It's so good.

543
00:21:51,358 --> 00:21:54,398
(The special dish, gochujang pork belly...)

544
00:21:55,868 --> 00:21:58,338
(is eaten with onions.)

545
00:21:59,438 --> 00:22:00,938
(Curious)

546
00:22:01,668 --> 00:22:04,008
(Favorable response)

547
00:22:04,708 --> 00:22:05,708
(Moaning)

548
00:22:08,038 --> 00:22:09,177
(Expressing the taste through his frown)

549
00:22:09,178 --> 00:22:10,248
It's so good.

550
00:22:11,308 --> 00:22:12,418
How is it so good?

551
00:22:13,218 --> 00:22:14,278
I'm going to gain weight.

552
00:22:15,118 --> 00:22:16,118
- Right?
- Yes.

553
00:22:16,119 --> 00:22:17,348
It's so tasty.

554
00:22:20,158 --> 00:22:22,588
(Staring)

555
00:22:24,028 --> 00:22:25,528
What a waste of that caravan.

556
00:22:25,728 --> 00:22:27,458
I honestly didn't care,

557
00:22:27,558 --> 00:22:31,267
but it suddenly occurred to me that we weren't using it.

558
00:22:31,268 --> 00:22:33,498
It's such a waste.

559
00:22:35,138 --> 00:22:37,738
(The day that Hyun Wook came)

560
00:22:38,678 --> 00:22:41,208
(Hyun Wook fell in love with the caravan.)

561
00:22:42,248 --> 00:22:43,978
(Loving it)

562
00:22:44,778 --> 00:22:47,348
(I thought it was a place of exile.)

563
00:22:47,748 --> 00:22:51,448
If Hyun Wook were to say,

564
00:22:51,588 --> 00:22:53,887
"I'll sleep in the caravan,"

565
00:22:53,888 --> 00:22:55,157
I would be so disappointed.

566
00:22:55,158 --> 00:22:57,157
Right. Because you'd be all alone in the house.

567
00:22:57,158 --> 00:22:59,027
- Yes. So, - Right.

568
00:22:59,028 --> 00:23:01,328
- I thought it was a place of exile.
- It's such a waste, though.

569
00:23:02,668 --> 00:23:04,027
Everyone wants to sleep in it.

570
00:23:04,028 --> 00:23:05,638
- It's so cozy.
- Indeed.

571
00:23:08,968 --> 00:23:13,078
I realized the gravity...

572
00:23:13,338 --> 00:23:14,738
of the situation today.

573
00:23:14,948 --> 00:23:16,548
But it's been that way every day.

574
00:23:16,648 --> 00:23:18,678
But we had less time today.

575
00:23:19,948 --> 00:23:20,978
We always lose our way.

576
00:23:21,178 --> 00:23:22,217
- Always?
- Because of the kids.

577
00:23:22,218 --> 00:23:23,318
- Because of the kids?
- Yes.

578
00:23:23,418 --> 00:23:25,217
- Tae Ri mostly led the class today.
- Yes.

579
00:23:25,218 --> 00:23:27,318
I think you can split it 50-50.

580
00:23:27,818 --> 00:23:30,528
- How?
- Split the burden 50-50.

581
00:23:30,888 --> 00:23:32,057
The burden of teaching.

582
00:23:32,058 --> 00:23:33,227
(He suggests that they share the burden.)

583
00:23:33,228 --> 00:23:34,968
You're practically the main teacher.

584
00:23:35,268 --> 00:23:37,527
That will make things easier for her, right?

585
00:23:37,528 --> 00:23:39,097
You need to step up.

586
00:23:39,098 --> 00:23:40,497
I don't know when.

587
00:23:40,498 --> 00:23:41,768
Just step up whenever.

588
00:23:42,538 --> 00:23:44,667
But today,

589
00:23:44,668 --> 00:23:47,077
- I also couldn't swoop in.
- Right.

590
00:23:47,078 --> 00:23:49,208
- I couldn't take over.
- Right.

591
00:23:49,308 --> 00:23:50,947
You have such a strong sense of responsibility...

592
00:23:50,948 --> 00:23:52,878
Yes. That's my problem!

593
00:23:53,778 --> 00:23:56,017
- Mine is that I'm too relaxed.
- I've always been...

594
00:23:56,018 --> 00:23:58,357
bad at entrusting others with tasks.

595
00:23:58,358 --> 00:24:01,357
Do that. You tend to do everything on your own.

596
00:24:01,358 --> 00:24:02,928
- Right.
- Stop doing that.

597
00:24:03,558 --> 00:24:05,157
When we plan things,

598
00:24:05,158 --> 00:24:08,158
we always do it together from here on out.

599
00:24:08,728 --> 00:24:09,798
We plan things together.

600
00:24:10,228 --> 00:24:11,568
We can just do it.

601
00:24:11,768 --> 00:24:13,038
Just step up.

602
00:24:13,438 --> 00:24:15,408
Let's prepare things together.

603
00:24:15,738 --> 00:24:19,277
At first, I suggested that we prepare for classes together,

604
00:24:19,278 --> 00:24:21,277
but you said it was too much,

605
00:24:21,278 --> 00:24:22,847
so we gradually reduced it. Right?

606
00:24:22,848 --> 00:24:25,017
- Is that right?
- I think so.

607
00:24:25,018 --> 00:24:26,877
You admitted it pretty fast. Really?

608
00:24:26,878 --> 00:24:29,147
- We must spend more time together.
- Let's finish the food...

609
00:24:29,148 --> 00:24:30,788
- Yes.
- and start preparing.

610
00:24:32,788 --> 00:24:33,988
Why did it get so quiet all of a sudden?

611
00:24:34,888 --> 00:24:36,788
Maybe around 9pm.

612
00:24:37,028 --> 00:24:38,798
We'll have a meeting for an hour.

613
00:24:39,758 --> 00:24:41,228
That fixes everything.

614
00:24:41,328 --> 00:24:43,068
But I thought...

615
00:24:44,368 --> 00:24:47,067
you two would be really close.

616
00:24:47,068 --> 00:24:48,337
How long have you known each other?

617
00:24:48,338 --> 00:24:50,468
We first met at "Twenty Five Twenty One."

618
00:24:50,568 --> 00:24:51,608
The drama.

619
00:24:52,208 --> 00:24:56,648
We've gotten pretty close right now.

620
00:24:56,748 --> 00:24:59,077
But he felt quite uncomfortable around me...

621
00:24:59,078 --> 00:25:01,378
because of our age gap and everything.

622
00:25:02,448 --> 00:25:04,617
I do find her a bit difficult.

623
00:25:04,618 --> 00:25:06,587
Is it because she's a senior actor?

624
00:25:06,588 --> 00:25:07,588
Yes.

625
00:25:08,058 --> 00:25:09,528
You should be close friends.

626
00:25:09,728 --> 00:25:11,087
I want to!

627
00:25:11,088 --> 00:25:12,297
Yes, open up to each other.

628
00:25:12,298 --> 00:25:13,928
I also want to be close friends.

629
00:25:14,028 --> 00:25:15,098
Start being friends today!

630
00:25:15,628 --> 00:25:16,668
- Do this.
- We've already made up,

631
00:25:16,898 --> 00:25:18,028
- right?
- You should do this.

632
00:25:18,938 --> 00:25:20,538
"It's okay."

633
00:25:20,838 --> 00:25:21,938
Let's do it.

634
00:25:22,308 --> 00:25:23,338
Go.

635
00:25:24,568 --> 00:25:27,178
(They hold hands as they're told.)

636
00:25:28,648 --> 00:25:30,107
- How do we do it?
- I don't know.

637
00:25:30,108 --> 00:25:32,218
Don't they go, "It's okay?"

638
00:25:32,918 --> 00:25:33,947
What is that?

639
00:25:33,948 --> 00:25:35,148
- You don't know this?
- No.

640
00:25:35,248 --> 00:25:37,888
But they did that. Like, "It's okay."

641
00:25:38,518 --> 00:25:39,958
Hold on. Let me ask.

642
00:25:40,558 --> 00:25:42,928
Wait, just like that. Let me make a phone call.

643
00:25:45,298 --> 00:25:46,597
You're making a phone call?

644
00:25:46,598 --> 00:25:48,598
It helps people reconcile.

645
00:25:49,128 --> 00:25:50,128
- Is it...
- Yes.

646
00:25:50,129 --> 00:25:52,167
- Like, "It's okay." - I hope it works.

647
00:25:52,168 --> 00:25:53,197
"It's okay."

648
00:25:53,198 --> 00:25:54,238
(Rummaging)

649
00:25:58,008 --> 00:26:00,608
Honey, what was that thing that we said, "It's okay?"

650
00:26:01,678 --> 00:26:02,678
It doesn't exist?

651
00:26:04,208 --> 00:26:06,778
You don't know? But we did that all the time when we were in Hawaii.

652
00:26:08,148 --> 00:26:11,647
"It's okay, friend. I'm sorry, and I love you."

653
00:26:11,648 --> 00:26:12,658
Okay.

654
00:26:13,088 --> 00:26:14,488
And they hold hands. Okay.

655
00:26:14,758 --> 00:26:15,788
Start.

656
00:26:15,988 --> 00:26:16,988
What are we supposed to say?

657
00:26:17,058 --> 00:26:18,058
What did I just say?

658
00:26:19,428 --> 00:26:20,428
Hang on.

659
00:26:20,758 --> 00:26:22,228
You both heard it, though.

660
00:26:22,468 --> 00:26:24,997
"It's okay, friend. I'm sorry, and I love you."

661
00:26:24,998 --> 00:26:28,297
Yes, "It's okay, friend. I'm sorry, and I love you."

662
00:26:28,298 --> 00:26:29,337
Okay, action.

663
00:26:29,338 --> 00:26:30,738
Say it with your heart. Look into each other's eyes.

664
00:26:31,568 --> 00:26:32,577
Start.

665
00:26:32,578 --> 00:26:33,708
(Shy)

666
00:26:34,578 --> 00:26:36,708
- It's okay, friend.
- Guys.

667
00:26:37,478 --> 00:26:38,577
Volume up.

668
00:26:38,578 --> 00:26:40,617
You tell the kids to speak louder,

669
00:26:40,618 --> 00:26:42,018
and your voices are tiny.

670
00:26:42,188 --> 00:26:43,188
Start.

671
00:26:43,189 --> 00:26:44,947
- It's okay, friend.
- It's okay, friend.

672
00:26:44,948 --> 00:26:46,687
- I'm sorry, and I love you.
- I'm sorry, and I love you.

673
00:26:46,688 --> 00:26:48,088
Okay.

674
00:26:48,188 --> 00:26:49,887
Doesn't it make you feel better?

675
00:26:49,888 --> 00:26:51,528
- It does.
- I knew it.

676
00:26:51,958 --> 00:26:54,528
We're going to do this every time a problem occurs, okay?

677
00:26:54,928 --> 00:26:56,168
- Sounds good.
- Yes.

678
00:26:56,228 --> 00:26:57,597
- Yes!
- Yes.

679
00:26:57,598 --> 00:26:59,038
- Yes!
- Yes.

680
00:27:00,038 --> 00:27:01,038
Should we go inside?

681
00:27:01,039 --> 00:27:02,138
- Yes.
- Yes.

682
00:27:02,608 --> 00:27:03,608
Let's go.

683
00:27:03,609 --> 00:27:05,278
(The dinner that solved lots of problems ends.)

684
00:27:07,108 --> 00:27:08,208
How long do we have left?

685
00:27:08,808 --> 00:27:10,377
We have five classes left.

686
00:27:10,378 --> 00:27:12,347
We're really running out of time.

687
00:27:12,348 --> 00:27:14,018
(An emergency meeting begins.)

688
00:27:14,478 --> 00:27:15,488
Are you going to shorten it?

689
00:27:16,648 --> 00:27:18,788
Rather than taking the lines out,

690
00:27:18,958 --> 00:27:20,117
we could summarize them.

691
00:27:20,118 --> 00:27:22,188
We can do that.

692
00:27:22,758 --> 00:27:24,988
We have to finish this fast.

693
00:27:25,088 --> 00:27:26,098
We should do it tonight.

694
00:27:26,258 --> 00:27:28,727
We have to give them out, and they must memorize them.

695
00:27:28,728 --> 00:27:29,798
Let's finish it tonight.

696
00:27:29,968 --> 00:27:32,737
I'll try shortening them.

697
00:27:32,738 --> 00:27:33,797
(They must revise the script tonight.)

698
00:27:33,798 --> 00:27:36,237
There were some difficulties...

699
00:27:36,238 --> 00:27:38,007
(What she felt after today's class)

700
00:27:38,008 --> 00:27:39,078
during class.

701
00:27:39,308 --> 00:27:40,337
The kids...

702
00:27:40,338 --> 00:27:41,437
(Will it be too much for the children?)

703
00:27:41,438 --> 00:27:42,977
They're too young,

704
00:27:42,978 --> 00:27:45,008
yet too much is handed to them.

705
00:27:46,048 --> 00:27:48,847
So, they can't process it all.

706
00:27:48,848 --> 00:27:50,688
(To meet them at eye level)

707
00:27:50,948 --> 00:27:52,857
Sniffle, sniffle.

708
00:27:52,858 --> 00:27:54,218
(She says the lines out loud.)

709
00:27:54,718 --> 00:27:55,827
(Toto: Don't desire it.)

710
00:27:55,828 --> 00:27:57,027
(Toto, Scarecrow)

711
00:27:57,028 --> 00:28:01,158
(Ms. Kim revises the lines one by one.)

712
00:28:02,798 --> 00:28:06,398
(Thinking about the kids,)

713
00:28:08,199 --> 00:28:12,669
(she revised the script until late at night.)

714
00:28:14,162 --> 00:28:17,732
(The revision is over,)

715
00:28:19,672 --> 00:28:24,242
(and she quietly walks into her room so as not to wake them up.)

716
00:28:29,252 --> 00:28:32,952
(Her day ended almost by sunrise.)

717
00:28:36,052 --> 00:28:40,262
(And a few hours later)

718
00:28:42,432 --> 00:28:45,962
(North Pole Teacher leaves to attend the wedding.)

719
00:28:47,002 --> 00:28:50,102
(Worn out)

720
00:28:52,502 --> 00:28:55,542
(And not long after)

721
00:28:56,912 --> 00:28:58,412
It rained last night.

722
00:28:59,082 --> 00:29:01,942
I heard it.

723
00:29:05,552 --> 00:29:09,222
(Potato Teacher also goes somewhere.)

724
00:29:12,362 --> 00:29:15,261
Are you wondering where I'm going on a weekend morning?

725
00:29:15,262 --> 00:29:16,932
(His monologue continues.)

726
00:29:18,462 --> 00:29:21,302
(He hums songs as he's excited about the weekend.)

727
00:29:22,002 --> 00:29:26,371
("HIGHER" by Koo Jun Hoe)

728
00:29:26,372 --> 00:29:28,842
I've watched "Twinkling Watermelon" at least ten times.

729
00:29:29,672 --> 00:29:30,712
I'm serious.

730
00:29:31,412 --> 00:29:32,412
It's such a good drama.

731
00:29:32,413 --> 00:29:33,782
(Hyun Wook is the lead role in "Twinkling Watermelon.")

732
00:29:34,042 --> 00:29:36,212
It's a drama about forming a band.

733
00:29:36,682 --> 00:29:39,182
They practice hard, get into fights,

734
00:29:39,422 --> 00:29:42,222
and do a performance after many hardships.

735
00:29:42,552 --> 00:29:45,892
They become one along the process.

736
00:29:46,392 --> 00:29:47,562
Just like our chant.

737
00:29:49,562 --> 00:29:51,892
(From today, we are one.)

738
00:29:52,862 --> 00:29:56,802
(We can do it. Let's go. Hooray!)

739
00:29:57,972 --> 00:29:59,972
My experiences are similar...

740
00:30:00,672 --> 00:30:04,612
those of the kids at Yongheung Elementary,

741
00:30:05,142 --> 00:30:07,781
and their process of learning how to act...

742
00:30:07,782 --> 00:30:10,452
in this show, "Curtain Up, Class!"

743
00:30:10,682 --> 00:30:14,222
I hope the kids learn what it feels like...

744
00:30:15,082 --> 00:30:19,561
when their hearts palpitate...

745
00:30:19,562 --> 00:30:20,792
through this experience.

746
00:30:22,862 --> 00:30:24,061
And I want them...

747
00:30:24,062 --> 00:30:26,501
(Potato Teacher's dream is for the kids' eyes to shine.)

748
00:30:26,502 --> 00:30:28,362
to work hard for their dreams.

749
00:30:29,872 --> 00:30:30,872
I mean it.

750
00:30:33,572 --> 00:30:37,042
(Potato Teacher arrives at a barbershop.)

751
00:30:37,872 --> 00:30:39,781
- Who is it?
- I'm here to get a haircut.

752
00:30:39,782 --> 00:30:40,782
- Come in.
- Okay.

753
00:30:41,242 --> 00:30:42,651
- Who's getting it?
- Me.

754
00:30:42,652 --> 00:30:43,681
Come in.

755
00:30:43,682 --> 00:30:45,721
(He suddenly wants a haircut.)

756
00:30:45,722 --> 00:30:46,722
Good morning.

757
00:30:47,552 --> 00:30:49,351
I've always gone to the hair salon...

758
00:30:49,352 --> 00:30:52,021
in front of my apartment complex when I was in elementary school.

759
00:30:52,022 --> 00:30:54,761
It wasn't exactly the same, but I still feel nostalgic...

760
00:30:54,762 --> 00:30:57,891
about the place, so I've been meaning to visit.

761
00:30:57,892 --> 00:30:58,902
(He visited a local barbershop to reminisce.)

762
00:31:00,462 --> 00:31:01,932
When did you first start?

763
00:31:02,002 --> 00:31:03,071
- Start what?
- This shop.

764
00:31:03,072 --> 00:31:04,102
- This shop?
- Yes.

765
00:31:04,432 --> 00:31:06,242
- It's been a while.
- Really?

766
00:31:06,402 --> 00:31:07,541
(A barbershop with an extensive history)

767
00:31:07,542 --> 00:31:08,772
Decades.

768
00:31:09,672 --> 00:31:13,141
- Do you see the brown hair?
- Yes.

769
00:31:13,142 --> 00:31:14,941
I want to dye them black.

770
00:31:14,942 --> 00:31:16,481
- This part?
- Yes.

771
00:31:16,482 --> 00:31:17,552
How long do you think it'll take?

772
00:31:17,682 --> 00:31:18,751
Ten minutes.

773
00:31:18,752 --> 00:31:20,582
- Ten minutes?
- It'll be done in ten minutes.

774
00:31:22,082 --> 00:31:23,591
Hair dye is fast nowadays.

775
00:31:23,592 --> 00:31:25,022
- That fast?
- Yes.

776
00:31:26,162 --> 00:31:27,192
Is this your first time in Mungyeong?

777
00:31:27,622 --> 00:31:28,622
- Mungyeong?
- Yes.

778
00:31:28,892 --> 00:31:31,361
I'm actually a teacher.

779
00:31:31,362 --> 00:31:33,132
- What kind?
- In acting.

780
00:31:33,732 --> 00:31:34,832
- Acting?
- Yes.

781
00:31:35,362 --> 00:31:37,231
Do you know Yongheung Elementary School?

782
00:31:37,232 --> 00:31:38,732
- Yes.
- You're a teacher there?

783
00:31:39,042 --> 00:31:41,302
- On November 11, - Yes.

784
00:31:41,742 --> 00:31:44,141
the kids are performing a play.

785
00:31:44,142 --> 00:31:45,942
- At the...
- During the school arts festival.

786
00:31:46,212 --> 00:31:48,112
- The school arts festival.
- Would you like to come?

787
00:31:48,542 --> 00:31:49,811
- To the school?
- Yes, to the school.

788
00:31:49,812 --> 00:31:51,511
- Why would old people go there?
- The school...

789
00:31:51,512 --> 00:31:53,251
To watch the kids' play.

790
00:31:53,252 --> 00:31:56,222
You cut my hair today, after all.

791
00:31:57,922 --> 00:31:59,521
We'll go if we're not busy, but we won't if we're busy.

792
00:31:59,522 --> 00:32:00,721
That's right. If we have customers...

793
00:32:00,722 --> 00:32:02,191
- You have to come if you're free.
- Sure.

794
00:32:02,192 --> 00:32:03,232
I'll be waiting.

795
00:32:03,592 --> 00:32:06,202
- Don't wait. I can't guarantee.
- Why not?

796
00:32:06,262 --> 00:32:07,302
I can't?

797
00:32:08,732 --> 00:32:10,531
- What do we do now?
- We paint your hair.

798
00:32:10,532 --> 00:32:11,802
Paint my hair?

799
00:32:12,202 --> 00:32:14,872
(Smiling at how chill he is)

800
00:32:16,142 --> 00:32:18,812
(Dyeing his hair black)

801
00:32:18,982 --> 00:32:20,241
You said it'd only take ten minutes?

802
00:32:20,242 --> 00:32:21,282
Yes.

803
00:32:21,612 --> 00:32:22,612
That's fast.

804
00:32:22,613 --> 00:32:23,682
(He turned into a black potato in 10 minutes.)

805
00:32:24,982 --> 00:32:27,122
Why do they take 30 to 40 minutes at salons, then?

806
00:32:32,492 --> 00:32:34,761
Is this okay, though? It's...

807
00:32:34,762 --> 00:32:37,191
- on my skin.
- It's fine.

808
00:32:37,192 --> 00:32:38,261
Will it come off?

809
00:32:38,262 --> 00:32:40,931
- It will.
- It will come off, right?

810
00:32:40,932 --> 00:32:42,001
Yes, it will.

811
00:32:42,002 --> 00:32:43,071
(Don't worry.)

812
00:32:43,072 --> 00:32:44,332
Where's the other teacher?

813
00:32:44,932 --> 00:32:46,141
She's resting.

814
00:32:46,142 --> 00:32:49,512
(A customer enters during their small talk.)

815
00:32:49,712 --> 00:32:51,771
- What's this?
- It's a show.

816
00:32:51,772 --> 00:32:52,982
They're filming a show.

817
00:32:54,012 --> 00:32:56,111
This barbershop must be getting popular.

818
00:32:56,112 --> 00:32:57,682
They're filming the shop.

819
00:32:57,712 --> 00:32:59,421
- Where from?
- I'm from Seoul.

820
00:32:59,422 --> 00:33:00,521
(Introducing himself)

821
00:33:00,522 --> 00:33:02,052
By the way, do you know Yongheung Elementary School?

822
00:33:02,522 --> 00:33:03,921
I'm from there.

823
00:33:03,922 --> 00:33:05,022
- Seriously?
- I'm from there.

824
00:33:05,322 --> 00:33:08,392
I'm teaching an acting class there.

825
00:33:08,862 --> 00:33:11,732
I'm a teacher there for two weeks.

826
00:33:11,792 --> 00:33:13,262
- Really?
- Yes.

827
00:33:14,162 --> 00:33:16,731
My nephews also go there.

828
00:33:16,732 --> 00:33:18,601
- Right now?
- Hyo Min, Ji Min...

829
00:33:18,602 --> 00:33:19,971
Hyo Min is preparing for a play.

830
00:33:19,972 --> 00:33:21,101
- Really?
- Yes.

831
00:33:21,102 --> 00:33:22,611
One of your nephews will be in a play.

832
00:33:22,612 --> 00:33:24,342
Please call Hyo Min today.

833
00:33:25,782 --> 00:33:27,511
To cheer him up.

834
00:33:27,512 --> 00:33:28,782
- Hyo Min?
- Yes.

835
00:33:29,212 --> 00:33:30,551
He needs some courage.

836
00:33:30,552 --> 00:33:32,422
He does. Help him out.

837
00:33:32,722 --> 00:33:34,282
- Thank you.
- Sure thing.

838
00:33:36,792 --> 00:33:38,221
- Wash your hair.
- Wash my hair?

839
00:33:38,222 --> 00:33:39,292
(It's been 10 minutes, so it's time to wash his hair.)

840
00:33:39,322 --> 00:33:41,662
- Are you going to wash it?
- Of course.

841
00:33:43,292 --> 00:33:44,592
You can lean on this.

842
00:33:46,232 --> 00:33:47,602
(Pressing)

843
00:33:50,732 --> 00:33:52,271
(This special shampoo zone never existed in his old barbershop.)

844
00:33:52,272 --> 00:33:54,302
(Relaxed)

845
00:33:55,002 --> 00:33:57,172
(Quiet)

846
00:33:58,412 --> 00:34:00,612
(She starts shampooing his hair.)

847
00:34:01,712 --> 00:34:03,712
(Coughing)

848
00:34:05,722 --> 00:34:08,522
(She may wash his hair for him, but he has to breathe on his own.)

849
00:34:10,652 --> 00:34:14,362
(This new type of experience makes him laugh.)

850
00:34:15,832 --> 00:34:19,102
(She thoroughly cleans every part of his head.)

851
00:34:22,202 --> 00:34:24,472
(Time to rinse it)

852
00:34:24,972 --> 00:34:28,072
(The stinging taste of soap goes straight into his nose.)

853
00:34:31,072 --> 00:34:33,142
(The dye on his sideburns didn't come off.)

854
00:34:34,442 --> 00:34:37,452
(I will not tolerate any residue.)

855
00:34:39,622 --> 00:34:42,022
(She ends up getting more shampoo.)

856
00:34:43,822 --> 00:34:47,462
(Let me rub it off for you.)

857
00:34:48,492 --> 00:34:51,192
(Rinsing for the last time)

858
00:34:53,032 --> 00:34:55,902
(These aren't his tears.)

859
00:34:58,932 --> 00:35:02,772
(She's done cleaning this potato.)

860
00:35:05,942 --> 00:35:09,252
(She uses one towel to dry his hair and face.)

861
00:35:09,812 --> 00:35:11,952
Wash your face with water.

862
00:35:13,882 --> 00:35:15,182
(Quietly washing his face)

863
00:35:15,482 --> 00:35:17,422
- Wash your face cleanly.
- Okay.

864
00:35:22,162 --> 00:35:23,162
Here.

865
00:35:23,163 --> 00:35:24,992
- Is this how it usually goes?
- Dry your hair.

866
00:35:25,802 --> 00:35:26,902
Come on.

867
00:35:28,002 --> 00:35:29,301
- You're going to be on TV.
- What?

868
00:35:29,302 --> 00:35:30,472
You're going to be on TV.

869
00:35:31,072 --> 00:35:32,232
Where is he?

870
00:35:33,472 --> 00:35:34,771
(This 25-year-old man looks prettier.)

871
00:35:34,772 --> 00:35:35,812
It looks good, right?

872
00:35:36,442 --> 00:35:38,042
It's gotten dark.

873
00:35:38,272 --> 00:35:39,382
That's amazing.

874
00:35:39,742 --> 00:35:40,912
All done.

875
00:35:42,182 --> 00:35:45,112
(Meanwhile, in the Mushroom House)

876
00:35:54,462 --> 00:35:57,362
(She wakes up to the sound of her morning alarm.)

877
00:35:58,262 --> 00:36:01,202
(Checking her phone)

878
00:36:02,902 --> 00:36:04,871
(Hyun Wook)

879
00:36:04,872 --> 00:36:06,871
(I put your clothes from Seoul by the door.)

880
00:36:06,872 --> 00:36:08,772
(Wear them and stay warm for the rest of your time here.)

881
00:36:11,712 --> 00:36:14,412
(Warm clothes for Tae Ri)

882
00:36:16,452 --> 00:36:19,152
(Touched)

883
00:36:21,682 --> 00:36:22,752
Hyun Wook.

884
00:36:26,592 --> 00:36:31,192
(He gave her clothes and left.)

885
00:36:33,332 --> 00:36:35,871
(Hyun Wook)

886
00:36:35,872 --> 00:36:42,042
(Thanks, where are you?)

887
00:36:42,572 --> 00:36:43,711
It's perfect.

888
00:36:43,712 --> 00:36:46,982
(He's busy getting a blowout.)

889
00:36:48,112 --> 00:36:49,882
- It looks neat.
- I know.

890
00:36:50,112 --> 00:36:51,512
You look good.

891
00:36:52,082 --> 00:36:54,382
- I'll teach Hyo Min well.
- Okay.

892
00:36:54,652 --> 00:36:56,221
My name is Potato Teacher.

893
00:36:56,222 --> 00:36:57,392
- Potato?
- Yes.

894
00:36:57,952 --> 00:36:59,522
Potato, not Sweet Potato?

895
00:37:00,892 --> 00:37:02,961
- He'll know my name.
- Okay.

896
00:37:02,962 --> 00:37:04,131
- Thank you.
- Potato Teacher.

897
00:37:04,132 --> 00:37:06,502
- You have a good image.
- Yes.

898
00:37:06,802 --> 00:37:08,261
- Thank you.
- Take care.

899
00:37:08,262 --> 00:37:09,801
- I'll see you again.
- Okay.

900
00:37:09,802 --> 00:37:11,702
- Bye, Potato Teacher.
- Bye.

901
00:37:11,932 --> 00:37:14,101
Goodbye.

902
00:37:14,102 --> 00:37:16,142
(Goodbye)

903
00:37:17,312 --> 00:37:19,642
(He finally checks his phone.)

904
00:37:20,012 --> 00:37:21,381
(Tae Ri: Thanks, where are you?)

905
00:37:21,382 --> 00:37:23,181
(I trimmed my hair at a barbershop.)

906
00:37:23,182 --> 00:37:26,321
(I'll be there soon.)

907
00:37:26,322 --> 00:37:27,751
(Do you want to go on a drive today?)

908
00:37:27,752 --> 00:37:31,051
(You know, get some fresh air.)

909
00:37:31,052 --> 00:37:32,251
(Sure, it's the weekend.)

910
00:37:32,252 --> 00:37:35,422
(Next, he'll go on a drive.)

911
00:37:38,062 --> 00:37:40,962
(In the meantime, Tae Ri...)

912
00:37:42,302 --> 00:37:46,872
(takes a walk around the town, wearing the clothes from Hyun Wook.)

913
00:37:50,372 --> 00:37:53,382
(She returns after one lap.)

914
00:37:56,012 --> 00:37:57,282
Hyun Wook, are you here?

915
00:37:58,712 --> 00:38:01,351
(Quiet)

916
00:38:01,352 --> 00:38:02,422
He's not.

917
00:38:04,952 --> 00:38:08,292
(On her way to the restroom)

918
00:38:08,522 --> 00:38:11,332
(Restroom)

919
00:38:12,962 --> 00:38:14,062
You scared me!

920
00:38:16,902 --> 00:38:18,002
You scared me!

921
00:38:19,302 --> 00:38:21,301
You scared me. Are you all right?

922
00:38:21,302 --> 00:38:22,302
- What?
- Are you all right?

923
00:38:22,303 --> 00:38:23,742
- Yes. I went for a walk.
- Where?

924
00:38:24,212 --> 00:38:25,342
I cooked.

925
00:38:25,442 --> 00:38:26,911
- You cooked?
- I mean, I got some food.

926
00:38:26,912 --> 00:38:28,141
Really? What did you get?

927
00:38:28,142 --> 00:38:29,412
- What?
- What did you get?

928
00:38:29,552 --> 00:38:31,251
Tea and...

929
00:38:31,252 --> 00:38:32,582
(Stuttering)

930
00:38:32,852 --> 00:38:35,082
- What?
- Are you in a rush?

931
00:38:35,952 --> 00:38:37,252
No, we can talk.

932
00:38:37,622 --> 00:38:39,051
No, go inside later.

933
00:38:39,052 --> 00:38:42,292
(No, go inside later.)

934
00:38:43,132 --> 00:38:45,661
(I see.)

935
00:38:45,662 --> 00:38:47,161
- Just...
- Okay.

936
00:38:47,162 --> 00:38:48,162
Oh, jeez.

937
00:38:48,462 --> 00:38:49,771
- I have to go.
- Yes?

938
00:38:49,772 --> 00:38:50,772
Yes.

939
00:38:51,272 --> 00:38:52,902
(Fanning)

940
00:38:53,602 --> 00:38:55,942
Don't film this. I'm serious.

941
00:38:57,112 --> 00:38:58,472
(Fanning)

942
00:38:59,142 --> 00:39:00,142
(Fanning)

943
00:39:00,143 --> 00:39:02,181
It's because I'm hot. I'm serious.

944
00:39:02,182 --> 00:39:03,252
(It's November, but I'm hot.)

945
00:39:03,382 --> 00:39:05,352
This really can't be on TV.

946
00:39:05,482 --> 00:39:09,492
(A stinky welcome to his first variety show)

947
00:39:12,052 --> 00:39:14,091
Give me one second. Let me spray something.

948
00:39:14,092 --> 00:39:15,492
- I'll...
- Go ahead.

949
00:39:19,132 --> 00:39:21,702
What should I spray, though? This is insane.

950
00:39:22,432 --> 00:39:24,032
- I have to go.
- All right.

951
00:39:24,272 --> 00:39:25,932
You can go inside.

952
00:39:26,602 --> 00:39:27,772
- See you.
- Okay.

953
00:39:29,672 --> 00:39:32,642
(Things could have gotten awkward once again.)

954
00:39:36,712 --> 00:39:37,712
Let's go.

955
00:39:37,713 --> 00:39:41,622
(Chauffeur Choi takes her on a drive this weekend.)

956
00:39:43,292 --> 00:39:45,922
(Snacks that Chauffeur Choi brought)

957
00:39:46,922 --> 00:39:48,391
- That's chamomile.
- Is this it?

958
00:39:48,392 --> 00:39:49,462
And that's ssanghwa tea.

959
00:39:51,862 --> 00:39:53,202
Is one of them yours?

960
00:39:53,262 --> 00:39:54,901
No, they're both yours. My drink is here.

961
00:39:54,902 --> 00:39:55,962
Okay.

962
00:40:03,142 --> 00:40:05,112
I guess there's a place called a cafe out there.

963
00:40:06,112 --> 00:40:08,212
- Yes.
- And a place called a barbershop.

964
00:40:10,752 --> 00:40:13,181
(He hits the road with Tae Ri, who needs outside air.)

965
00:40:13,182 --> 00:40:14,352
You didn't get much sleep, did you?

966
00:40:15,652 --> 00:40:17,491
It's worse.

967
00:40:17,492 --> 00:40:18,791
(She barely slept.)

968
00:40:18,792 --> 00:40:20,721
I couldn't stop thinking about it.

969
00:40:20,722 --> 00:40:24,232
You know, like when a thought haunts you.

970
00:40:24,362 --> 00:40:25,492
What kind of thought?

971
00:40:26,802 --> 00:40:28,902
I couldn't stop thinking about the classes.

972
00:40:30,002 --> 00:40:31,932
You need to sleep well, though.

973
00:40:32,432 --> 00:40:36,972
I think the burden of responsibility is too heavy.

974
00:40:37,572 --> 00:40:41,111
If I make a mistake or ruin things,

975
00:40:41,112 --> 00:40:42,112
Yes.

976
00:40:42,512 --> 00:40:44,812
I'll end up wasting such precious time.

977
00:40:46,582 --> 00:40:48,651
These ten classes...

978
00:40:48,652 --> 00:40:50,551
(She wants to give them as much as she can...)

979
00:40:50,552 --> 00:40:51,651
(during this short period.)

980
00:40:51,652 --> 00:40:54,322
I know better than anyone...

981
00:40:55,762 --> 00:40:57,591
that you feel a huge sense of responsibility.

982
00:40:57,592 --> 00:40:59,832
But you could take things a little easier.

983
00:41:00,702 --> 00:41:04,272
I wonder if things will get better by taking it easy.

984
00:41:06,372 --> 00:41:08,801
You know, have fun with it.

985
00:41:08,802 --> 00:41:10,512
(He wants her to feel less burdened.)

986
00:41:10,972 --> 00:41:12,071
Okay.

987
00:41:12,072 --> 00:41:13,741
- You can do it.
- Yes.

988
00:41:13,742 --> 00:41:18,551
Just thinking about the future, I think you can do it.

989
00:41:18,552 --> 00:41:20,151
(He tries to comfort her.)

990
00:41:20,152 --> 00:41:21,452
Yes. Good.

991
00:41:24,522 --> 00:41:26,022
I'll have to cheer up.

992
00:41:30,032 --> 00:41:31,261
This is a different road.

993
00:41:31,262 --> 00:41:32,661
(Tae Ri and Potato enter a mountain road.)

994
00:41:32,662 --> 00:41:33,662
It is.

995
00:41:36,062 --> 00:41:39,232
What scene did you film at the place we're going to?

996
00:41:39,842 --> 00:41:42,401
In the first episode, there's a scene of my character...

997
00:41:42,402 --> 00:41:44,372
- when she was 19.
- Okay.

998
00:41:44,912 --> 00:41:47,381
It was probably that scene.

999
00:41:47,382 --> 00:41:48,442
I see.

1000
00:41:51,852 --> 00:41:53,121
- It's so far.
- It is.

1001
00:41:53,122 --> 00:41:56,292
(Driving along a twisty mountain path)

1002
00:41:59,422 --> 00:42:01,492
(Impressed)

1003
00:42:02,692 --> 00:42:04,092
- Beautiful.
- Yes.

1004
00:42:06,732 --> 00:42:10,031
(The autumn scene makes her naturally take pictures.)

1005
00:42:10,032 --> 00:42:11,632
There are so many cool mountains.

1006
00:42:18,472 --> 00:42:19,681
Aren't you tired?

1007
00:42:19,682 --> 00:42:22,182
You should get some sleep. If you feel like it.

1008
00:42:22,682 --> 00:42:25,412
I feel bad about sleeping while you're driving.

1009
00:42:26,112 --> 00:42:29,052
That's fine. You need to get some sleep while you still can.

1010
00:42:33,422 --> 00:42:35,591
Let me rest my eyes for a minute.

1011
00:42:35,592 --> 00:42:36,632
Sure.

1012
00:42:37,792 --> 00:42:38,992
You can listen to music.

1013
00:42:39,092 --> 00:42:40,601
(Muting the music)

1014
00:42:40,602 --> 00:42:41,702
You can listen to it.

1015
00:42:46,472 --> 00:42:49,242
(Blocking the sunlight in case it's too bright)

1016
00:42:50,772 --> 00:42:51,772
(Going over a speed bump)

1017
00:42:51,773 --> 00:42:53,642
(Looking at her)

1018
00:42:55,312 --> 00:42:56,481
(Another speed bump)

1019
00:42:56,482 --> 00:42:58,912
(Looking at her again)

1020
00:43:00,982 --> 00:43:06,222
(He drives carefully so that she can sleep soundly.)

1021
00:43:13,232 --> 00:43:17,032
(A good nap)

1022
00:43:19,202 --> 00:43:20,672
- Was it pretty on our way here?
- What?

1023
00:43:20,772 --> 00:43:22,302
- Was it pretty on our way here?
- It was.

1024
00:43:24,342 --> 00:43:26,542
I can check it out on our way back.

1025
00:43:28,912 --> 00:43:29,981
(Arriving at their destination)

1026
00:43:29,982 --> 00:43:31,282
- Thanks for driving.
- No problem.

1027
00:43:35,222 --> 00:43:36,392
It's pretty windy.

1028
00:43:38,952 --> 00:43:42,092
(They're welcome by the autumn breeze here.)

1029
00:43:42,762 --> 00:43:43,762
Here.

1030
00:43:43,763 --> 00:43:44,861
(Giving her a hand warmer)

1031
00:43:44,862 --> 00:43:45,862
Thanks.

1032
00:43:46,832 --> 00:43:48,361
You've been awfully kind since yesterday.

1033
00:43:48,362 --> 00:43:50,231
(You've been awfully kind since yesterday, Hyun Wook.)

1034
00:43:50,232 --> 00:43:51,232
Hyun Wook.

1035
00:43:51,233 --> 00:43:52,402
- Me?
- Yes.

1036
00:43:52,672 --> 00:43:54,971
- I've always been kind.
- You've become so kind.

1037
00:43:54,972 --> 00:43:56,542
Right.

1038
00:43:58,412 --> 00:43:59,882
You're going to make my heart race.

1039
00:44:01,142 --> 00:44:03,712
(Tae Ri and Potato visited...)

1040
00:44:04,412 --> 00:44:07,151
(Choganjeong Garden)

1041
00:44:07,152 --> 00:44:09,082
"You may look around."

1042
00:44:09,822 --> 00:44:11,052
"Push."

1043
00:44:13,192 --> 00:44:16,392
(Open the weathered gate,)

1044
00:44:19,532 --> 00:44:22,832
(and there's a secluded pavilion, sitting in serenity.)

1045
00:44:24,232 --> 00:44:25,501
Oh, my gosh!

1046
00:44:25,502 --> 00:44:26,871
(Choganjeong Garden is a pavilion built...)

1047
00:44:26,872 --> 00:44:28,171
(by a scholar of the Joseon Dynasty, and it is a famous scenic spot...)

1048
00:44:28,172 --> 00:44:29,371
(where dense forests and magnificent rock formations create a view.)

1049
00:44:29,372 --> 00:44:30,742
This place is lovely.

1050
00:44:32,772 --> 00:44:34,041
That was here?

1051
00:44:34,042 --> 00:44:35,942
(The reason it means more to Tae Ri)

1052
00:44:38,082 --> 00:44:42,421
(In her first drama, "Mr. Sunshine")

1053
00:44:42,422 --> 00:44:43,492
Yes, my lady.

1054
00:44:44,392 --> 00:44:47,562
(It's where she first appeared as Go Ae Shin, a noblewoman.)

1055
00:44:48,692 --> 00:44:52,032
I couldn't believe it was the same place.

1056
00:44:53,002 --> 00:44:54,902
It was breathtaking.

1057
00:44:55,732 --> 00:44:56,831
So beautiful.

1058
00:44:56,832 --> 00:44:58,001
(This place was a first for her.)

1059
00:44:58,002 --> 00:45:02,942
At the time, Lee Jung Eun was incredibly helpful.

1060
00:45:03,272 --> 00:45:06,681
She played a role that was always...

1061
00:45:06,682 --> 00:45:08,881
with my character, a noblewoman.

1062
00:45:08,882 --> 00:45:10,511
(Actress Lee Jung Eun acted with her.)

1063
00:45:10,512 --> 00:45:12,252
Should I go and check if it's working?

1064
00:45:14,752 --> 00:45:17,692
I asked Jung Eun a lot of questions then.

1065
00:45:17,792 --> 00:45:21,591
Having her around was really helpful.

1066
00:45:21,592 --> 00:45:22,721
I relied on her.

1067
00:45:22,722 --> 00:45:24,632
(Her memories of relying on Jung Eun are here.)

1068
00:45:26,232 --> 00:45:29,031
I should have made some pinwheels to bring with us.

1069
00:45:29,032 --> 00:45:30,032
(Returning to the spot with Hyun Wook years later)

1070
00:45:31,172 --> 00:45:33,341
Was that your first drama series? "Mr. Sunshine?"

1071
00:45:33,342 --> 00:45:34,342
Yes.

1072
00:45:35,702 --> 00:45:37,412
I didn't know anything back then.

1073
00:45:37,872 --> 00:45:39,412
How were you so good?

1074
00:45:40,782 --> 00:45:41,942
You must be born with it.

1075
00:45:43,182 --> 00:45:44,212
You were born to be a star.

1076
00:45:45,552 --> 00:45:47,852
I mean it. I'm not trying to flatter you.

1077
00:45:48,452 --> 00:45:52,422
A star shouldn't have such weak willpower.

1078
00:45:52,722 --> 00:45:53,761
Come on.

1079
00:45:53,762 --> 00:45:55,362
You don't have weak willpower.

1080
00:45:56,992 --> 00:45:58,931
I still get so nervous even now.

1081
00:45:58,932 --> 00:46:01,231
(I still get so nervous even now.)

1082
00:46:01,232 --> 00:46:02,301
Even with drama series?

1083
00:46:02,302 --> 00:46:05,002
(Even with drama series?)

1084
00:46:05,332 --> 00:46:09,442
I think I'm definitely better than before,

1085
00:46:09,542 --> 00:46:11,471
but if there is something I find difficult...

1086
00:46:11,472 --> 00:46:14,041
or something I feel like...

1087
00:46:14,042 --> 00:46:16,141
I need to put in more work,

1088
00:46:16,142 --> 00:46:17,182
I get super nervous.

1089
00:46:18,352 --> 00:46:22,582
That's when the tips of my fingers turn ice cold,

1090
00:46:23,052 --> 00:46:25,392
and I start shaking.

1091
00:46:27,692 --> 00:46:31,292
We're working with children now.

1092
00:46:32,232 --> 00:46:33,601
It's really hard.

1093
00:46:33,602 --> 00:46:35,162
(The reason why Ms. Kim works hard on preparing her classes)

1094
00:46:36,432 --> 00:46:38,632
My cousin is an elementary school teacher.

1095
00:46:39,202 --> 00:46:40,372
- Really?
- Yes.

1096
00:46:42,002 --> 00:46:43,842
Did you ask her for tips?

1097
00:46:43,942 --> 00:46:45,212
Not at all.

1098
00:46:45,912 --> 00:46:46,912
Why not?

1099
00:46:49,182 --> 00:46:52,212
I think I spent about a week by myself instead.

1100
00:46:52,452 --> 00:46:54,252
- While preparing?
- Yes.

1101
00:46:55,052 --> 00:46:57,091
You're so different from me.

1102
00:46:57,092 --> 00:46:59,292
(You're so different from me.)

1103
00:46:59,492 --> 00:47:03,261
I went everywhere and asked everyone.

1104
00:47:03,262 --> 00:47:04,662
(Tae Ri prepared herself by asking for advice.)

1105
00:47:06,262 --> 00:47:08,502
I wonder...

1106
00:47:10,202 --> 00:47:12,731
what would have happened...

1107
00:47:12,732 --> 00:47:15,042
if I had just faced it straight on.

1108
00:47:17,212 --> 00:47:19,542
I'm not sure. I don't know what the right way is.

1109
00:47:19,642 --> 00:47:21,682
- There is no such thing.
- Right.

1110
00:47:25,212 --> 00:47:27,752
When we shot "Twenty Five Twenty One,"

1111
00:47:29,782 --> 00:47:32,152
you were so nervous at first.

1112
00:47:33,162 --> 00:47:34,422
I was surprised.

1113
00:47:34,622 --> 00:47:35,761
(Hyun Wook was also nervous at the time.)

1114
00:47:35,762 --> 00:47:38,292
I didn't think you were the type to get nervous.

1115
00:47:39,092 --> 00:47:40,862
- That...
- You don't get nervous now, right?

1116
00:47:41,062 --> 00:47:42,802
- I do.
- Do you?

1117
00:47:44,102 --> 00:47:46,902
We weren't close during "Twenty Five Twenty One."

1118
00:47:47,572 --> 00:47:48,902
Not at all.

1119
00:47:50,272 --> 00:47:52,512
To be honest, you didn't open up to me.

1120
00:47:54,782 --> 00:47:56,882
I was a fan of Kim Tae Ri then.

1121
00:47:57,482 --> 00:47:59,282
(What is he saying?)

1122
00:47:59,552 --> 00:48:01,081
How can I approach you when I'm a fan?

1123
00:48:01,082 --> 00:48:02,422
It was difficult.

1124
00:48:03,192 --> 00:48:06,092
Yes, it was difficult when I look back now.

1125
00:48:06,692 --> 00:48:07,992
I was really young.

1126
00:48:09,322 --> 00:48:11,161
You need life experience...

1127
00:48:11,162 --> 00:48:13,431
- to learn how to react.
- Yes.

1128
00:48:13,432 --> 00:48:15,531
- But I didn't know how.
- Yes.

1129
00:48:15,532 --> 00:48:18,301
Whenever it got awkward or uncomfortable,

1130
00:48:18,302 --> 00:48:22,701
I just avoided the situation.

1131
00:48:22,702 --> 00:48:23,711
Sure.

1132
00:48:23,712 --> 00:48:24,712
(After much thought, he chose to avoid.)

1133
00:48:27,342 --> 00:48:29,312
I totally understand.

1134
00:48:30,252 --> 00:48:34,282
I've known you for several years now.

1135
00:48:35,322 --> 00:48:36,622
I love it...

1136
00:48:38,222 --> 00:48:40,092
when you're being yourself.

1137
00:48:41,392 --> 00:48:44,831
Then I started to see the funny side of you.

1138
00:48:44,832 --> 00:48:45,832
(He cannot hide his sloppy side.)

1139
00:48:45,833 --> 00:48:48,932
(Laughing)

1140
00:48:49,262 --> 00:48:51,871
I think I like it the more I get to know you.

1141
00:48:51,872 --> 00:48:54,501
(The more I get to know you, the more I like you.)

1142
00:48:54,502 --> 00:48:58,072
But it's another story when we have to live together.

1143
00:49:01,142 --> 00:49:02,241
It's definitely different.

1144
00:49:02,242 --> 00:49:03,582
(He cannot deny it.)

1145
00:49:03,682 --> 00:49:04,682
Very different.

1146
00:49:07,022 --> 00:49:08,851
We end up learning things we don't need to know.

1147
00:49:08,852 --> 00:49:11,892
(Being happy roommates means you see each other's everything.)

1148
00:49:12,692 --> 00:49:15,322
Anyway, I'm happy because you're kind since yesterday.

1149
00:49:18,692 --> 00:49:20,702
After being like that with you for a few days,

1150
00:49:24,232 --> 00:49:25,301
I decided to be nice.

1151
00:49:25,302 --> 00:49:29,472
(I'll be good to you.)

1152
00:49:31,272 --> 00:49:33,682
(Me too!)

1153
00:49:34,242 --> 00:49:35,442
Should we do that thing?

1154
00:49:37,312 --> 00:49:39,451
I can't do things like this.

1155
00:49:39,452 --> 00:49:43,492
(As the older one, Tae Ri reaches out first.)

1156
00:49:45,622 --> 00:49:48,361
(Holding hands face to face)

1157
00:49:48,362 --> 00:49:49,392
Happy?

1158
00:49:50,162 --> 00:49:52,332
- Hey, friend.
- Thank you.

1159
00:49:52,532 --> 00:49:55,361
- I'm sorry, and I love you.
- I'm sorry, and I love you.

1160
00:49:55,362 --> 00:49:57,802
(Hey, friend. Thank you. I'm sorry, and I love you.)

1161
00:49:59,732 --> 00:50:02,741
(It's a bit awkward, but they're sincerely connecting.)

1162
00:50:02,742 --> 00:50:04,612
Where did he learn this from?

1163
00:50:04,712 --> 00:50:05,872
I don't know.

1164
00:50:08,842 --> 00:50:13,112
(Two very different people met.)

1165
00:50:14,752 --> 00:50:19,352
(They faced many ups and downs as teachers.)

1166
00:50:22,822 --> 00:50:26,432
(But they began to learn more about each other.)

1167
00:50:27,332 --> 00:50:31,602
(They're the most reliable person to each other now.)

1168
00:50:36,342 --> 00:50:39,742
In the beginning, what made you want...

1169
00:50:40,442 --> 00:50:42,312
to do this show?

1170
00:50:45,212 --> 00:50:46,552
Was it a challenge for you?

1171
00:50:47,652 --> 00:50:49,352
Absolutely.

1172
00:50:49,622 --> 00:50:50,992
It's my first variety show too.

1173
00:50:54,292 --> 00:50:56,622
I think it's almost just as big...

1174
00:50:57,132 --> 00:51:00,961
as shooting a drama series.

1175
00:51:00,962 --> 00:51:02,101
- Doing this?
- Yes.

1176
00:51:02,102 --> 00:51:04,402
But we shoot series over months.

1177
00:51:04,702 --> 00:51:05,732
That's true.

1178
00:51:09,202 --> 00:51:11,072
But I think this is a work of art too.

1179
00:51:12,012 --> 00:51:14,242
- Me too.
- It's art.

1180
00:51:16,642 --> 00:51:18,081
It's a documentation of our growth.

1181
00:51:18,082 --> 00:51:20,082
- It's going on our filmography.
- Absolutely.

1182
00:51:23,752 --> 00:51:28,422
(The teachers are growing along with the changing leaves.)

1183
00:51:33,532 --> 00:51:37,072
(The night is falling on this peaceful weekend.)

1184
00:51:39,972 --> 00:51:41,771
(It's quiet at the Mushroom House.)

1185
00:51:41,772 --> 00:51:42,772
Where is it?

1186
00:51:42,772 --> 00:51:43,772
(Is there an intruder at the Mushroom House?)

1187
00:51:43,773 --> 00:51:45,512
Where do I get my weapons?

1188
00:51:48,412 --> 00:51:49,611
This must be it.

1189
00:51:49,612 --> 00:51:50,812
(Is he trying to break in?)

1190
00:51:57,357 --> 00:51:58,596
This must be it.

1191
00:51:58,597 --> 00:51:59,727
(Is he trying to break in?)

1192
00:52:03,127 --> 00:52:06,167
Hello. I'm CODE KUNST or CO KUN. Nice to meet you.

1193
00:52:06,767 --> 00:52:08,337
I came here as the music director...

1194
00:52:08,437 --> 00:52:10,807
for the after-school acting class.

1195
00:52:11,277 --> 00:52:14,676
First off, I love children.

1196
00:52:14,677 --> 00:52:16,107
I like kids.

1197
00:52:16,307 --> 00:52:17,447
Also,

1198
00:52:17,547 --> 00:52:21,846
the purpose of the show is heartwarming.

1199
00:52:21,847 --> 00:52:24,516
I joined while hoping I could be of help.

1200
00:52:24,517 --> 00:52:26,217
(He joined the acting class hoping he could help.)

1201
00:52:27,487 --> 00:52:28,527
Hello.

1202
00:52:28,987 --> 00:52:30,427
Hello.

1203
00:52:30,527 --> 00:52:32,356
I know it was last-minute,

1204
00:52:32,357 --> 00:52:34,466
so thank you for accepting.

1205
00:52:34,467 --> 00:52:35,767
I should do it no matter what.

1206
00:52:37,027 --> 00:52:40,267
I'll make the songs fast, and go over soon to help.

1207
00:52:40,367 --> 00:52:41,467
I'd love that!

1208
00:52:41,807 --> 00:52:42,906
Thank you.

1209
00:52:42,907 --> 00:52:44,676
(Ms. Kim,)

1210
00:52:44,677 --> 00:52:48,177
(I'm here to make music.)

1211
00:52:48,977 --> 00:52:50,277
This place is nice.

1212
00:52:50,747 --> 00:52:52,177
- What?
- Did the bell ring?

1213
00:52:54,187 --> 00:52:56,917
(Quick to welcome)

1214
00:52:58,557 --> 00:53:00,687
(Passing a mysterious piece of paper)

1215
00:53:01,857 --> 00:53:02,887
Hurry.

1216
00:53:03,897 --> 00:53:07,126
You were the first one to ring our bell,

1217
00:53:07,127 --> 00:53:08,327
so we couldn't hear it.

1218
00:53:09,167 --> 00:53:10,167
Hello.

1219
00:53:10,737 --> 00:53:11,966
You live in a nice house.

1220
00:53:11,967 --> 00:53:13,166
We wrote this. Would you read this?

1221
00:53:13,167 --> 00:53:15,606
"Welcome to Heart Shiitake Mushroom House."

1222
00:53:15,607 --> 00:53:17,236
Is this Heart Shiitake Mushroom House?

1223
00:53:17,237 --> 00:53:18,237
Yes.

1224
00:53:18,507 --> 00:53:19,536
Welcome.

1225
00:53:19,537 --> 00:53:22,907
(Welcome to the Mushroom House.)

1226
00:53:23,707 --> 00:53:26,776
Gosh! It's Heart Shiitake Mushroom House!

1227
00:53:26,777 --> 00:53:28,086
(Entering the Mushroom House)

1228
00:53:28,087 --> 00:53:29,816
It's Heart Shiitake Mushroom House.

1229
00:53:29,817 --> 00:53:31,386
Please use these.

1230
00:53:31,387 --> 00:53:33,156
(Welcome slippers)

1231
00:53:33,157 --> 00:53:34,987
This place has great welfare.

1232
00:53:35,927 --> 00:53:38,327
- It's decorated so nicely.
- This way.

1233
00:53:38,957 --> 00:53:40,997
You can put your bags down here.

1234
00:53:41,367 --> 00:53:44,396
Your jacket. Give me your jacket.

1235
00:53:44,397 --> 00:53:46,136
(Mushroom House Welfare List: welcome slippers, coat check)

1236
00:53:46,137 --> 00:53:47,236
Yes.

1237
00:53:47,237 --> 00:53:48,767
(Bowing)

1238
00:53:49,667 --> 00:53:51,376
Would you like some tea right now?

1239
00:53:51,377 --> 00:53:52,977
Yes, sure. Anything is fine.

1240
00:53:53,777 --> 00:53:55,806
You can take them off and go up.

1241
00:53:55,807 --> 00:53:56,807
(Butler Choi mode)

1242
00:53:57,107 --> 00:53:58,116
- The middle.
- Please sit in the middle.

1243
00:53:58,117 --> 00:53:59,377
The Mushroom House is nice.

1244
00:54:01,187 --> 00:54:02,187
Have some cookies.

1245
00:54:02,188 --> 00:54:03,817
(Butler Choi mode again)

1246
00:54:05,787 --> 00:54:06,917
There are some apples too.

1247
00:54:11,127 --> 00:54:13,357
I haven't been treated this well in a long time.

1248
00:54:14,627 --> 00:54:16,226
It's her idea.

1249
00:54:16,227 --> 00:54:17,896
- I love it.
- Yes.

1250
00:54:17,897 --> 00:54:19,396
(He loves the welfare system at Mushroom House.)

1251
00:54:19,397 --> 00:54:20,906
This is for you.

1252
00:54:20,907 --> 00:54:22,606
(Passing him the new script she fixed overnight)

1253
00:54:22,607 --> 00:54:23,807
It was just finished.

1254
00:54:25,637 --> 00:54:27,847
Gosh, it looks like you work hard.

1255
00:54:28,707 --> 00:54:31,746
If you look at the back, there is a list of sounds.

1256
00:54:31,747 --> 00:54:33,077
(A list of sounds is ready.)

1257
00:54:33,147 --> 00:54:34,287
I'm really curious about the music.

1258
00:54:34,787 --> 00:54:36,047
- The music?
- Yes.

1259
00:54:36,117 --> 00:54:39,356
We can move over to the gym and start.

1260
00:54:39,357 --> 00:54:42,326
While the two of you talk over there,

1261
00:54:42,327 --> 00:54:44,796
I'll work on braised short ribs.

1262
00:54:44,797 --> 00:54:46,027
- Braised short ribs?
- Yes.

1263
00:54:46,557 --> 00:54:48,567
I'm going to get ready.

1264
00:54:48,767 --> 00:54:50,696
- It takes a long time.
- Okay.

1265
00:54:50,697 --> 00:54:52,736
Are you pressured?

1266
00:54:52,737 --> 00:54:54,767
- It takes long. Over an hour.
- An hour.

1267
00:54:54,907 --> 00:54:55,907
Okay.

1268
00:54:55,908 --> 00:54:56,937
(Cooking Master Potato's braised short ribs coming soon!)

1269
00:54:58,677 --> 00:55:01,147
(Rushing over)

1270
00:55:03,007 --> 00:55:04,617
- Is this the school?
- Yes.

1271
00:55:05,417 --> 00:55:08,317
I'll show you around later.

1272
00:55:09,387 --> 00:55:10,587
You sound like a realtor.

1273
00:55:13,357 --> 00:55:14,726
- It has a good layout.
- Really?

1274
00:55:14,727 --> 00:55:16,587
- It has a big yard.
- Yes.

1275
00:55:16,687 --> 00:55:18,756
Also, you can hear children laugh...

1276
00:55:18,757 --> 00:55:20,967
during lunchtime.

1277
00:55:21,827 --> 00:55:23,666
It's rare to get that kind of a feature in a home.

1278
00:55:23,667 --> 00:55:25,236
Exactly.

1279
00:55:25,237 --> 00:55:27,367
(They're a perfect match.)

1280
00:55:27,667 --> 00:55:29,867
Gosh, we're going to a school at night.

1281
00:55:31,237 --> 00:55:32,277
How cute.

1282
00:55:32,807 --> 00:55:34,646
The smell of a gym!

1283
00:55:34,647 --> 00:55:36,247
(Entering with endless words of admiration)

1284
00:55:36,647 --> 00:55:38,277
This takes me back.

1285
00:55:41,587 --> 00:55:42,687
It's Scarecrow's hat.

1286
00:55:43,117 --> 00:55:44,357
It looks like Harry Potter's.

1287
00:55:45,487 --> 00:55:46,987
Yes.

1288
00:55:47,927 --> 00:55:49,087
It suits you so well.

1289
00:55:50,487 --> 00:55:51,526
Do I look like Scarecrow?

1290
00:55:51,527 --> 00:55:52,527
(He was born to be Scarecrow.)

1291
00:55:53,757 --> 00:55:54,766
Yes, you do.

1292
00:55:54,767 --> 00:55:55,767
(Scarecrow CO KUN makes Tae Ri laugh.)

1293
00:55:55,768 --> 00:55:56,797
Great.

1294
00:55:57,367 --> 00:55:58,866
I brought this.

1295
00:55:58,867 --> 00:56:00,136
(Starting their music discussion)

1296
00:56:00,137 --> 00:56:01,307
Shall we listen to this?

1297
00:56:02,637 --> 00:56:05,207
I made this one for when the characters move.

1298
00:56:05,777 --> 00:56:08,377
(Tae Ri's order 1: song for the road)

1299
00:56:08,547 --> 00:56:09,576
Something a bit like...

1300
00:56:09,577 --> 00:56:12,376
(Singing)

1301
00:56:12,377 --> 00:56:13,377
Do you want it to be cheerful?

1302
00:56:13,378 --> 00:56:15,987
Yes. Something exciting and fun.

1303
00:56:16,287 --> 00:56:17,287
Something cheerful?

1304
00:56:17,288 --> 00:56:20,417
(What did he come up with?)

1305
00:56:20,657 --> 00:56:21,827
One, two...

1306
00:56:23,387 --> 00:56:25,597
(It makes Tae Ri bounce.)

1307
00:56:25,897 --> 00:56:26,957
We can then add the footsteps.

1308
00:56:28,927 --> 00:56:31,136
They will act as the drums.

1309
00:56:31,137 --> 00:56:32,366
(They plan to add the sound of the children's footsteps.)

1310
00:56:32,367 --> 00:56:34,106
- Like this.
- Gosh, they'll love this.

1311
00:56:34,107 --> 00:56:35,437
Do you think so?

1312
00:56:36,567 --> 00:56:37,606
And...

1313
00:56:37,607 --> 00:56:39,106
(Feeling excited from the start)

1314
00:56:39,107 --> 00:56:41,576
This one is for the witch.

1315
00:56:41,577 --> 00:56:43,306
(Tae Ri's order 2: song for the witch)

1316
00:56:43,307 --> 00:56:45,377
- It has to be scary, right?
- Yes.

1317
00:56:46,847 --> 00:56:48,787
(Singing)

1318
00:56:49,487 --> 00:56:51,186
- I think I get it.
- It can be really scary.

1319
00:56:51,187 --> 00:56:52,586
Can it be really scary?

1320
00:56:52,587 --> 00:56:53,757
- Yes.
- Okay.

1321
00:56:55,087 --> 00:56:58,157
(How did he make a song out of her screeching?)

1322
00:57:00,257 --> 00:57:02,667
(Standing ovation)

1323
00:57:04,867 --> 00:57:07,197
I love it.

1324
00:57:10,237 --> 00:57:12,376
(The communication was successful.)

1325
00:57:12,377 --> 00:57:14,406
I added the laughter for now.

1326
00:57:14,407 --> 00:57:16,476
(While CO KUN is outputting everything as she wanted...)

1327
00:57:16,477 --> 00:57:18,546
If you add sugar...

1328
00:57:18,547 --> 00:57:19,976
to your braised beef short ribs...

1329
00:57:19,977 --> 00:57:22,787
(Hyun Wook is busy inputting the braised short rib recipe.)

1330
00:57:22,947 --> 00:57:24,557
Today's secret recipe.

1331
00:57:24,757 --> 00:57:26,857
Add half a paper cup of sugar.

1332
00:57:29,057 --> 00:57:31,427
Half a cup.

1333
00:57:32,827 --> 00:57:35,767
Half a cup.

1334
00:57:40,097 --> 00:57:42,367
(One more time)

1335
00:57:42,467 --> 00:57:43,837
Half a cup.

1336
00:57:44,677 --> 00:57:47,807
(There is a major error with his output.)

1337
00:57:48,677 --> 00:57:50,546
Add half a paper cup of sugar.

1338
00:57:50,547 --> 00:57:52,647
(Double-checking: Add half a paper cup of sugar)

1339
00:57:52,717 --> 00:57:54,547
Gosh, it wasn't half a cup of water.

1340
00:57:56,187 --> 00:57:59,057
(There is a communication error from the beginning.)

1341
00:58:00,257 --> 00:58:03,057
(Next, he's making an onion and pear juice.)

1342
00:58:04,727 --> 00:58:05,827
How do I use this?

1343
00:58:07,497 --> 00:58:08,497
Why isn't it working?

1344
00:58:09,427 --> 00:58:11,097
(Turning slightly)

1345
00:58:12,767 --> 00:58:15,737
(Nothing is going smoothly.)

1346
00:58:17,537 --> 00:58:19,276
(After using the blender, sift it through a strainer.)

1347
00:58:19,277 --> 00:58:21,177
(After using the blender, sift it through a strainer?)

1348
00:58:22,807 --> 00:58:27,117
(He miraculously threw out what he needed.)

1349
00:58:27,817 --> 00:58:31,286
(The braised short rib hasn't seen any progress.)

1350
00:58:31,287 --> 00:58:33,317
I hope they will take...

1351
00:58:33,857 --> 00:58:35,387
as much time as possible over there.

1352
00:58:36,157 --> 00:58:37,997
I hope they'll get too absorbed in the music.

1353
00:58:38,597 --> 00:58:40,027
They won't notice time passing...

1354
00:58:40,627 --> 00:58:41,867
thanks to their millions of ideas.

1355
00:58:46,067 --> 00:58:48,267
(Absorbed)

1356
00:58:49,167 --> 00:58:50,167
Bells.

1357
00:58:50,707 --> 00:58:51,737
How refreshing.

1358
00:58:52,537 --> 00:58:53,537
What is this? It's so good.

1359
00:58:53,538 --> 00:58:54,646
(Luckily, they are really absorbed.)

1360
00:58:54,647 --> 00:58:56,047
(Pleased smile)

1361
00:58:56,077 --> 00:58:57,646
Now, the scene where they meet the Cowardly Lion.

1362
00:58:57,647 --> 00:58:59,916
The lion? How should I make a song for him?

1363
00:58:59,917 --> 00:59:01,087
(Next up is the song for the lion.)

1364
00:59:01,217 --> 00:59:03,686
The lion is a coward,

1365
00:59:03,687 --> 00:59:04,717
- Yes.
- right?

1366
00:59:08,387 --> 00:59:09,956
- I like that.
- A talk show lion?

1367
00:59:09,957 --> 00:59:11,226
(A talk show lion?)

1368
00:59:11,227 --> 00:59:14,057
Let us welcome the lion!

1369
00:59:16,697 --> 00:59:19,567
(Is it a Western-style song now?)

1370
00:59:20,697 --> 00:59:23,507
I feel like the lion will appear in front of a sunset.

1371
00:59:24,277 --> 00:59:25,577
I should work on the lion.

1372
00:59:26,107 --> 00:59:27,507
I'll be able to do it fast.

1373
00:59:28,647 --> 00:59:31,276
I'll try drawing it out in my head tonight.

1374
00:59:31,277 --> 00:59:32,377
Okay.

1375
00:59:33,347 --> 00:59:34,817
Then it looks like...

1376
00:59:35,587 --> 00:59:37,186
a lot of things will be filled up.

1377
00:59:37,187 --> 00:59:38,487
(Looking forward to a richer play with music)

1378
00:59:38,517 --> 00:59:40,086
Okay. Shall we go and eat braised short ribs?

1379
00:59:40,087 --> 00:59:41,127
Sounds good.

1380
00:59:42,557 --> 00:59:44,086
Let's go back home!

1381
00:59:44,087 --> 00:59:47,197
(Meanwhile, the braised short ribs back at the Mushroom House is...)

1382
00:59:51,367 --> 00:59:52,497
(Sighing)

1383
00:59:52,767 --> 00:59:55,737
(It's being boiled down with his sighs.)

1384
00:59:56,037 --> 00:59:57,037
What?

1385
00:59:57,038 --> 00:59:58,377
(Sniffing)

1386
00:59:59,007 --> 01:00:01,247
(High expectations)

1387
01:00:01,447 --> 01:00:03,606
- It smells pretty good.
- It really does.

1388
01:00:03,607 --> 01:00:04,777
It smells cool.

1389
01:00:05,517 --> 01:00:07,276
(Luckily, it smells ready.)

1390
01:00:07,277 --> 01:00:08,487
- CO KUN.
- Yes?

1391
01:00:08,517 --> 01:00:09,717
Will you taste it?

1392
01:00:11,017 --> 01:00:14,227
This means you're confident, right?

1393
01:00:14,687 --> 01:00:15,687
I'm not sure.

1394
01:00:18,827 --> 01:00:21,967
(Will it taste just as cool?)

1395
01:00:23,297 --> 01:00:25,336
Add more water and sugar.

1396
01:00:25,337 --> 01:00:26,497
- Sugar?
- Yes.

1397
01:00:28,167 --> 01:00:31,307
(Urgently pouring water)

1398
01:00:31,977 --> 01:00:34,407
(Sprinkling sugar)

1399
01:00:35,507 --> 01:00:36,547
About that much?

1400
01:00:37,647 --> 01:00:38,717
Well...

1401
01:00:38,847 --> 01:00:41,386
Most people add about this much.

1402
01:00:41,387 --> 01:00:42,447
- Really?
- Yes.

1403
01:00:43,287 --> 01:00:45,217
About this much sugar goes into braised short ribs.

1404
01:00:45,517 --> 01:00:46,757
- Really?
- Yes.

1405
01:00:47,317 --> 01:00:48,386
Add more.

1406
01:00:48,387 --> 01:00:50,627
(Going crazy)

1407
01:00:51,127 --> 01:00:53,727
(Moved by how bold Hyun Wook is)

1408
01:00:54,327 --> 01:00:55,926
How much longer will it take?

1409
01:00:55,927 --> 01:00:57,496
Now. It's done now.

1410
01:00:57,497 --> 01:00:58,737
- Is it?
- Yes.

1411
01:00:58,937 --> 01:01:00,597
It just finished.

1412
01:01:04,277 --> 01:01:06,907
(Hastily finishing it off with sesame seeds)

1413
01:01:09,747 --> 01:01:12,147
(Pouring)

1414
01:01:12,917 --> 01:01:15,687
(Moved once again)

1415
01:01:16,587 --> 01:01:17,587
(Covered in sesame seeds)

1416
01:01:17,588 --> 01:01:18,987
Who pours sesame seeds like that?

1417
01:01:21,327 --> 01:01:22,527
I don't care anymore.

1418
01:01:24,827 --> 01:01:26,127
- Tae Ri.
- Yes?

1419
01:01:27,027 --> 01:01:28,097
It's really amazing.

1420
01:01:29,367 --> 01:01:31,237
Gosh, this is fantastic.

1421
01:01:31,337 --> 01:01:32,637
You're right.

1422
01:01:32,737 --> 01:01:33,866
The braised short ribs look great.

1423
01:01:33,867 --> 01:01:34,906
(He somehow finished it.)

1424
01:01:34,907 --> 01:01:36,166
It looks so cool.

1425
01:01:36,167 --> 01:01:38,707
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you for the food.

1426
01:01:38,877 --> 01:01:39,936
Thank you for the food.

1427
01:01:39,937 --> 01:01:41,547
Tae Ri, try a rib.

1428
01:01:43,207 --> 01:01:44,947
(Biting)

1429
01:01:48,687 --> 01:01:51,456
(How will CO-Potato's first dish taste?)

1430
01:01:51,457 --> 01:01:52,487
How is it?

1431
01:01:52,501 --> 01:01:54,271
(Biting)

1432
01:01:58,011 --> 01:02:00,710
(How will CO-Potato's first dish taste?)

1433
01:02:00,711 --> 01:02:01,811
How is it?

1434
01:02:01,951 --> 01:02:03,650
- It's good.
- Is it good?

1435
01:02:03,651 --> 01:02:04,721
It's good.

1436
01:02:05,051 --> 01:02:06,051
Have some.

1437
01:02:06,052 --> 01:02:07,891
(Taps of encouragement for hardworking Hyun Wook)

1438
01:02:08,351 --> 01:02:09,820
(Biting)

1439
01:02:09,821 --> 01:02:11,560
- It's good.
- It's not bad.

1440
01:02:11,561 --> 01:02:12,660
Really? I'll taste it.

1441
01:02:12,661 --> 01:02:14,961
(Co-chef CO KUN takes a bite.)

1442
01:02:15,491 --> 01:02:16,831
- It's much better now.
- Yes.

1443
01:02:18,931 --> 01:02:19,931
Did something happen?

1444
01:02:21,831 --> 01:02:22,900
There was a process.

1445
01:02:22,901 --> 01:02:24,071
(A process we cannot share)

1446
01:02:24,241 --> 01:02:26,070
Gosh, how long did this take?

1447
01:02:26,071 --> 01:02:27,711
- Didn't it take over two hours?
- Almost.

1448
01:02:28,941 --> 01:02:31,011
- This dish takes a long time.
- Yes.

1449
01:02:32,181 --> 01:02:33,811
North Pole Teacher cooks well too.

1450
01:02:34,411 --> 01:02:35,810
North Pole Teacher?

1451
01:02:35,811 --> 01:02:38,150
I think people become better at cooking after marriage.

1452
01:02:38,151 --> 01:02:39,581
Although they were not good at it in the past. It's amazing.

1453
01:02:43,491 --> 01:02:46,461
(North Pole Teacher is returning with his hands full.)

1454
01:02:48,561 --> 01:02:49,591
Gosh.

1455
01:02:52,001 --> 01:02:53,001
- Gosh.
- Hey.

1456
01:02:53,002 --> 01:02:55,231
- Hello. Gosh.
- What?

1457
01:02:55,501 --> 01:02:57,470
- Hey! You came back so soon!
- It's our first time meeting.

1458
01:02:57,471 --> 01:02:59,771
- Did I come back early?
- I heard you'd return at 11pm.

1459
01:03:00,171 --> 01:03:02,371
- Let's eat this. Fried chicken.
- Hey, throw this out.

1460
01:03:03,971 --> 01:03:04,980
It's better to throw it out.

1461
01:03:04,981 --> 01:03:05,981
(Suddenly exiled)

1462
01:03:05,982 --> 01:03:07,880
- It's nice to meet you.
- I...

1463
01:03:07,881 --> 01:03:09,510
- Gosh.
- Hello.

1464
01:03:09,511 --> 01:03:11,120
I'm always following you.

1465
01:03:11,121 --> 01:03:12,251
Please sit down.

1466
01:03:12,881 --> 01:03:14,650
- Did you eat dinner?
- Yes.

1467
01:03:14,651 --> 01:03:16,720
- You eat. This is...
- There are three boxes of chicken.

1468
01:03:16,721 --> 01:03:18,720
There's a famous chicken place in Mungyeong.

1469
01:03:18,721 --> 01:03:19,920
Eat this one too.

1470
01:03:19,921 --> 01:03:21,191
I need to get changed.

1471
01:03:24,031 --> 01:03:25,101
It looks good.

1472
01:03:26,201 --> 01:03:27,671
It's visually powerful, isn't it?

1473
01:03:29,501 --> 01:03:32,541
It has lost its spark a bit.

1474
01:03:33,271 --> 01:03:34,410
It looks gloomy.

1475
01:03:34,411 --> 01:03:36,371
It feels really gloomy.

1476
01:03:37,511 --> 01:03:38,680
(Unbelievable)

1477
01:03:38,681 --> 01:03:40,011
I'm here again.

1478
01:03:41,411 --> 01:03:42,411
It's crazy.

1479
01:03:43,711 --> 01:03:46,221
It feels like home now. It's cozy.

1480
01:03:47,791 --> 01:03:49,320
Let's eat.

1481
01:03:49,321 --> 01:03:50,751
(Their first dinner together)

1482
01:03:50,921 --> 01:03:53,120
- Try the braised short ribs.
- Sure. Who made it?

1483
01:03:53,121 --> 01:03:54,760
- We made it together.
- Really?

1484
01:03:54,761 --> 01:03:55,790
It's tasty.

1485
01:03:55,791 --> 01:03:57,031
- Right?
- Yes.

1486
01:03:57,561 --> 01:03:58,701
It's so good.

1487
01:04:00,701 --> 01:04:02,271
The chicken has gone cold.

1488
01:04:02,571 --> 01:04:03,601
Yes.

1489
01:04:05,641 --> 01:04:07,341
- But it's still good.
- Yes, it's good.

1490
01:04:09,671 --> 01:04:11,140
At the wedding,

1491
01:04:11,141 --> 01:04:12,141
- I thought...
- You did great.

1492
01:04:12,142 --> 01:04:13,740
- it was my wedding.
- You did a great job.

1493
01:04:13,741 --> 01:04:15,550
I greeted all 300 people.

1494
01:04:15,551 --> 01:04:16,911
"Hello."

1495
01:04:19,921 --> 01:04:22,821
(Even though he's complaining,)

1496
01:04:26,561 --> 01:04:30,331
(he actually went all the way to Seoul for his friend.)

1497
01:04:32,701 --> 01:04:36,101
(He's a nice person, sincerely congratulating his friend.)

1498
01:04:38,101 --> 01:04:41,041
(He's a best friend to the groom's father too.)

1499
01:04:42,671 --> 01:04:44,380
Okay. Anyway.

1500
01:04:44,381 --> 01:04:46,080
(Kangnam is a good person.)

1501
01:04:46,081 --> 01:04:47,710
- What year were you born?
- In 1989.

1502
01:04:47,711 --> 01:04:48,751
In 1989? I see.

1503
01:04:49,381 --> 01:04:50,551
You're two years younger than me.

1504
01:04:51,051 --> 01:04:52,081
You were born in 1987.

1505
01:04:53,621 --> 01:04:55,321
Born in 1987, 1990, and 2002.

1506
01:04:55,691 --> 01:04:56,951
You look very mature, though.

1507
01:04:57,891 --> 01:04:59,060
- Your life as a producer...
- I've been through a lot.

1508
01:04:59,061 --> 01:05:00,221
You've been through a lot.

1509
01:05:01,291 --> 01:05:02,490
You look so mature.

1510
01:05:02,491 --> 01:05:04,031
Maybe it's because I hang out with older male friends a lot.

1511
01:05:04,331 --> 01:05:05,500
I work with them mostly.

1512
01:05:05,501 --> 01:05:06,501
- Producers?
- Yes.

1513
01:05:06,502 --> 01:05:08,330
- I was so jealous yesterday.
- Why?

1514
01:05:08,331 --> 01:05:09,431
- Because...
- Yes.

1515
01:05:10,201 --> 01:05:12,940
Tae Ri really loves Hyun Wook as a younger brother.

1516
01:05:12,941 --> 01:05:14,240
- As a younger brother.
- I see.

1517
01:05:14,241 --> 01:05:16,370
Later... Has it been four years since you've known each other?

1518
01:05:16,371 --> 01:05:17,711
- About 4 or 5 years.
- Yes.

1519
01:05:18,341 --> 01:05:20,280
I met him when he was 20 years old.

1520
01:05:20,281 --> 01:05:21,311
- Exactly.
- Right.

1521
01:05:21,451 --> 01:05:23,510
Since we met through "Twenty Five Twenty One,"

1522
01:05:23,511 --> 01:05:25,780
she has cared for me like this.

1523
01:05:25,781 --> 01:05:26,851
Exactly.

1524
01:05:27,021 --> 01:05:29,390
I do care for her too,

1525
01:05:29,391 --> 01:05:31,121
but I don't show it that well.

1526
01:05:31,291 --> 01:05:32,391
- I see.
- It's...

1527
01:05:32,821 --> 01:05:33,920
When I look back,

1528
01:05:33,921 --> 01:05:35,030
- I didn't express my feelings.
- I see.

1529
01:05:35,031 --> 01:05:36,330
- I was shy to do so.
- Right.

1530
01:05:36,331 --> 01:05:38,130
But when I don't show it,

1531
01:05:38,131 --> 01:05:40,201
I always regret it after a while.

1532
01:05:40,601 --> 01:05:41,801
"I should have shown it back then."

1533
01:05:42,001 --> 01:05:44,641
Instead of regretting it, I should've expressed my gratitude.

1534
01:05:44,871 --> 01:05:46,601
It's a shame to waste time.

1535
01:05:47,071 --> 01:05:49,670
We only have a limited time where we can express it.

1536
01:05:49,671 --> 01:05:50,711
- That's true.
- Yes.

1537
01:05:50,971 --> 01:05:52,241
How do you do it, though?

1538
01:05:52,341 --> 01:05:54,080
Should I say, "I really care for you, Tae Ri?"

1539
01:05:54,081 --> 01:05:56,181
You don't have to say it right away.

1540
01:05:56,481 --> 01:05:58,650
Don't say, "I really care for you" up front right away.

1541
01:05:58,651 --> 01:05:59,980
When the time passes,

1542
01:05:59,981 --> 01:06:01,350
there will be times...

1543
01:06:01,351 --> 01:06:03,291
- when you're moved.
- Right.

1544
01:06:03,521 --> 01:06:06,991
At that moment, tell her, instead of keeping it in your mind.

1545
01:06:07,221 --> 01:06:08,361
That's good advice.

1546
01:06:08,961 --> 01:06:10,391
That's mature talk.

1547
01:06:10,831 --> 01:06:12,731
You have to open up.

1548
01:06:13,201 --> 01:06:14,331
After coming here,

1549
01:06:15,031 --> 01:06:16,031
I've opened up a lot, I think.

1550
01:06:16,032 --> 01:06:18,171
- I believe so.
- You really have to open up.

1551
01:06:18,201 --> 01:06:19,440
(Agreeing)

1552
01:06:19,441 --> 01:06:21,341
By the way, it's my first time meeting you.

1553
01:06:21,571 --> 01:06:22,871
You've maintained a great shape.

1554
01:06:22,971 --> 01:06:25,241
- It's been a while now.
- Exactly.

1555
01:06:25,341 --> 01:06:26,511
What do you do other than personal training?

1556
01:06:26,611 --> 01:06:28,080
Personal training, pilates...

1557
01:06:28,081 --> 01:06:29,350
- Do you do pliates?
- Yes.

1558
01:06:29,351 --> 01:06:30,651
And soccer and running. Four things.

1559
01:06:31,451 --> 01:06:33,081
- You run?
- Running.

1560
01:06:33,451 --> 01:06:34,551
If you run,

1561
01:06:34,721 --> 01:06:36,150
- then...
- You shouldn't talk about running.

1562
01:06:36,151 --> 01:06:37,190
- Why?
- They'll get serious.

1563
01:06:37,191 --> 01:06:39,561
It's too late. They heard it already.

1564
01:06:39,821 --> 01:06:41,390
- They heard it.
- So...

1565
01:06:41,391 --> 01:06:44,861
During the pre-production meeting, I said I liked to run.

1566
01:06:45,101 --> 01:06:46,801
- I said, "I love running." - And...

1567
01:06:47,101 --> 01:06:49,271
- They dragged us somewhere...
- Did they?

1568
01:06:49,371 --> 01:06:50,700
with five vans.

1569
01:06:50,701 --> 01:06:51,800
(Going with five vans)

1570
01:06:51,801 --> 01:06:52,900
- One of them...
- Like "Squid Game?"

1571
01:06:52,901 --> 01:06:54,040
- Seriously.
- One was responsible...

1572
01:06:54,041 --> 01:06:55,571
for setting up cameras.

1573
01:06:56,971 --> 01:06:59,041
(Since the pre-production meeting, he has shown...)

1574
01:06:59,641 --> 01:07:01,881
(his crazy love for running.)

1575
01:07:02,451 --> 01:07:03,510
(Running)

1576
01:07:03,511 --> 01:07:04,880
(Running again)

1577
01:07:04,881 --> 01:07:06,050
(Running again)

1578
01:07:06,051 --> 01:07:07,451
(Running again)

1579
01:07:08,221 --> 01:07:10,151
